Texts.Chs: "...死亡侨民不会完全死去.许多人的结局都在大疗养院里, 在没有感觉的恐惧中慢慢枯萎. (这还没被公开过.)少数人的结局非常迅速: 转变成一种携带翅膀和知识的生物, 还有一种结局也许是升华, 成为一枚卵或者之类的东西. 这个值一千元以及邪恶和罪恶的诱惑..."
Texts.Eng: "...tomb-colonists do not exactly die. Many end in the Grand Sanatorium, withering slowly to insensate horror. (This is not publicised.) A few end in Emergence: transformation to a flimsy thing of wings and knowledge, an end in ecstacy, the delight of becoming an egg, of sorts. This is accounted a grand and vile and tempting sin..."

Texts.Chs: "概念就像砖头一样.他可以用来建造理性的法院.或者用它来砸窗户."
Texts.Eng: "A concept is a brick. It can be used to build a courthouse of reason. Or it can be thrown through the window."

Texts.Chs: "醒目的月蓝, 记忆和最明亮的珊瑚的蓝色."
Texts.Eng: "A wakes APOCYAN, the blue of memory and brightest coral."

Texts.Chs: "無法逃避的結局!" 一件发射鱼叉的强力武器.
Texts.Eng: "AN INESCAPABLE ENDING!" A potent weapon which permits Flensing attacks.

Texts.Chs: "给我带来海胆的核心,作为我的王."
Texts.Eng: "And bring me a Fluke-Core. For my Kin."

Texts.Chs: "在你的镜子之中, V 代表琉璃绿, 半梦半醒的颜色."
Texts.Eng: "Behind your mirror, V names VIRIC, the colour of shallow sleep."

Texts.Chs: "带给我一个警觉的雕像, 做我的新主教," 珊瑚之源说
Texts.Eng: "Bring me a Wakeful Idol, to be my new Bishop," the Principles said

Texts.Chs: "带给我一小块燧石, 作为我的卒," 珊瑚之源说
Texts.Eng: "Bring me a little flint, to be my new Paw," the Principles said

Texts.Chs: "给我带来怪物的牙齿, 作为我新的骑士.", 珊瑚之源说
Texts.Eng: "Bring me a monster's tooth, to be my new Night.", the Principles said

Texts.Chs: "心壳银, 作为我的新堡垒", 珊瑚之源说.
Texts.Eng: "Bring me heart-shelled silver, to be my new Root", the Principles said.

Texts.Chs: "星海黄色的C字母,记忆中太阳的颜色. 那些丰饶的,发出臭气的,真菌类的生物: 这些全都在星海黄的光辉中茁壮成长."
Texts.Eng: "C lights COSMOGONE, the colour of remembered suns. The fecund, the foetid, the fungal: these flourish in the glow of cosmogone."

Texts.Chs: "卡米努斯试验场: 靠后点站." 一件野蛮而令人恐惧的武器.
Texts.Eng: "Caminus Yards: Stand Well Back." A weapon of savage and alarming power.

Texts.Chs: "卡米努斯试验场: 我们一直爱着你." 这件强力的武器可以轻松撕开海兽的防护.
Texts.Eng: "Caminus Yards: We Have Always Loved You." A powerful weapon that permits Flensing attacks.

Texts.Chs: "不要再做這件事了." 卡特洛尔 & 哈瑟萨奇公司的新型号.
Texts.Eng: "DON'T DO IT AGAIN." One of C&H's newer models.

Texts.Chs: "畏惧她的利刃!" 李德彼特&斯坦罗德公司最可靠的一款,不用提太多. 允许你进行鱼叉攻击.
Texts.Eng: "Fear her touch!" One of L&S' more reliable pieces, which isn't saying much. Permits Flensing attacks.

Texts.Chs: "G代表着消逝的刚特褐灰, 是所有其他颜色被吞噬后所剩下的遗骸. 刚特褐灰可以在无尽的阴影中找到."
Texts.Eng: "G is lost in GANT, which remains when all other colours are eaten. Gant can be found where shadows are myriad."

Texts.Chs: "这里记录了一些穿越[xxxxx] 的细节,在[xxxxxx]的陪伴执行, 在 [xxxxxx]上...." [用这个提高你的交流值.未来的船长可以一直使用它除非你将它卖掉.]
Texts.Eng: "Herein are recorded certain details of a Voyage through [xxxxx] in the company of [xxxxxx], on [xxxxxx]...." [Use this to increase your Pages. Unless you sell it, future captains will have access to it.]

Texts.Chs: "我是自己命运的主人: 我是自己灵魂的船长." [你现在处于无情模式, 除了游戏基础的自动保存之外没有其他的储存槽位.如果你切换到仁慈模式你将失去这枚印章.]
Texts.Eng: "I am the master of my fate: I am the captain of my soul." [You are in Unforgiving mode, with no save slots besides the basic autosave. You will lose this token if you switch from Unforgiving to Merciful mode.]

Texts.Chs: "我必须把这个秘密藏在指尖王到不了的地方. 我希望在那之后他们不会继续打扰我. 所以我把它放在了寒霜城. 不是寒霜城的正中心. 我没疯. 但是,恩,它离寒霜城的正中心很近." [找到北方的寒霜城, 在倒数第二间密室找到机械师的秘密.]
Texts.Eng: "I had to hide the Secret somewhere the Fingerkings couldn't go. I hoped they'd leave me alone then. So I put it in Frostfound. Not the very heart of Frostfound. I'm not insane. But, um, quite close to the heart." [Find Frostfound, in the north, and retrieve the Mechanic's secret from the penultimate chamber.]

Texts.Chs: "I代表靛紫.没人记得为什么.靛紫为家中被遗忘的角落染色."
Texts.Eng: "I is for IRRIGO. No one remembers why. Irrigo colours the forgotten corners of home."

Texts.Chs: "我在制造引擎的时候需要帮助.它需要是活着的, 比如那石猪, 还有我, 呃, 很擅长金工." [从智慧监狱营救或者赎出来他, 智慧监狱位于汗国附近的莲花海中.他能帮助机械师完成工程.]
Texts.Eng: "I'll need help to build the engine. It'll need to be alive, like the Pigs, and I'm, er, better at metal." [Rescue or ransom him from Wisdom, in the Sea of Lilies near the Khanate to help the Tireless Mechanic complete his project.]

Texts.Chs: "這是個怪獸,你難道不這麼認為嗎?" 一件强力的鱼雷发射器.
Texts.Eng: "IT'S A MONSTER. ARE YOU?" A powerful weapon that relies on Torpedo attacks.

Texts.Chs:
"就像一道横梁跨越海泽,
横跨所有黄金年代!" [一件对寻找敌人非常有用的设备.]
Texts.Eng:
"Like a lane of beams athwart the sea,
Thro' all the circle of the golden year!" [An effective device for seeking enemies.]

Texts.Chs: "哦,是的, 今晚那个淹死的人在哼唱, 一首水中的歌就像鱼骨一样."
Texts.Eng: "Oh yes, the Drowned Man is humming tonight, a song in the water like the bones of fish."

Texts.Chs: "凡人啊,記住你將終有一死"
Texts.Eng: "Omnia mors perimit et nulli miseretur"

Texts.Chs: "P字母用黯蓝书写, 最深的海中的颜色. [有人在页边潦草的写道: 在大門之後是一片更無光的海]"
Texts.Eng: "P drowns in PELIGIN, the colour of the deepest zee. [Someone has scrawled in the margin: BEYOND THE GATE THERE IS A SEA MORE SUNLESS]"

Texts.Chs: "波阿狄西亞: 更強馬力,更低價格." 李德彼特&斯坦罗德公司能提供的最好产品,尽管通常情况下他们会偷工减料.
Texts.Eng: "THE BOADICEA: MORE POWER, LESS SUBTLETY." The best Leadbeater & Stainrod can supply, although as usual they've skimped on materials.

Texts.Chs: "用这个这就对了." 一个足够对付小型海兽和菜鸟海盗的武器.
Texts.Eng: "THIS WAY UP." A weapon which may serve against small monsters or feeble pirates.

Texts.Chs: "文登湾有这样一个小地方..."
Texts.Eng: "There's this little place in Venderbight..."

Texts.Chs: "这些就是驱动着巴扎的力量." 涡轮机运转着,发出巨量的热量.
Texts.Eng: "These are the forces that drive the Bazaar." The Impeller runs very, very hot.

Texts.Chs: "V 代表着黯紫罗兰,这血液的颜色要从尖端流出. 黯紫罗兰色的墨水用来签署最令人绝望的条约..."
Texts.Eng: "V marks VIOLANT when blood is shed in a spired place. Violant ink is employed for the most desperate treaties..."

Texts.Chs: "我們將密切關注." 这件武器的威力令人赞叹.
Texts.Eng: "WE SHALL COMPEL ATTENTION." A weapon of respectable power.

Texts.Chs: "把綠色的死水攪個天翻地覆!" 允许进行鱼雷攻击.
Texts.Eng: "WINNOW THE SLUMBERING GREEN!" Permits Torpedo attacks.

Texts.Chs: "我们需要曾经活着过的怪物材料. 因为我们没法拿到巴扎的心 (不,我们真的做不到), 我们会需要从黎明机器那里拿来的一些东西. 抱歉."[带来一个黎明元素, 一桶蓝宝石, 还有四十单位的阴暗黑骨, 带着机械师的秘密和令人不安的贤者,去噬王者的城堡.]
Texts.Eng: "We need once-living monster-material. And since we can't get the heart of the Bazaar (no, we really can't), we'll need something from the Dawn Machine. Sorry."[Take one Element of Dawn, one Casket of Sapphires, and forty units of Stygian Ivory, along with the Mechanic's Secret and the Unsettling Sage, to Kingeater's Castle.]

Texts.Chs: "你需要一些人去查看里面." [法布尔鼠助手对于气动老鼠传输机来说必不可少.]
Texts.Eng: "You wants someone to take a look inside that." [In combat, Rattus Faber Assistants can be deployed for quicker repairs. It's dangerous work. Don't expect them back.]

Texts.Chs: '蛀船虫' 鱼雷发射器轻便而致命.不要小瞧它们.
Texts.Eng: 'Seaworm' torpedoes are small but lethal. Don't underestimate them.

Texts.Chs:
'怪物猎人能找到并筛选出那些现实中的恐怖生物.她已经屠灭了深渊中发出光的生物, 在对海泽盛宴的回忆中吃掉了它的血肉, 用它的尸骨做成了武器.她曾经是个人类.' 
但是这个怪物猎人已经为辉煌的结局做好了准备. 黑色逐日者正在等待着.
Texts.Eng:
'The Monster-Hunter winnows the lesser terrors from the true. She has slain That Which Makes Light in the Deeps, eaten its flesh in remembrance of certain Feasts of the Zee, and fashioned her weapon from its remains. She was human, once.' 
But this Monster-Hunter is ready for a glorious ending. Icarus in Black awaits.

Texts.Chs: 1|"有个问题正在等着. 它在一艘早已沉没的船中游荡. 找到它."~2|"野兽被拴住了 - 但不会被永远拴住. 难民们会去伦敦." ~3|"曾经有七个人. 将来也会再次有七个人. 他们的名字也许会变, 但是七这个数字会留下来." ~4|"尼达继承人的名字会以玛利开头 - 那是个反抗者." ~5|"波浪之下, 还活着两座城市. 他们成长着. 他们很饿."~6|"小心安忒. 它会改变你. 你会变得锐利, 像刀’s刃一样."~7|"伤口会再次打开; 血肉无法治疗. 将你的同情与悔恨带去." ~8|"他们渴望着: 自由, 平等, 永恒."~9|"他们只是凡人. 他们也会受苦: 生命, 疾病, 死亡."~10|"牧师去往钟塔. 那钟. 那 哦,天啊. 那好可怕." ~11|"他们害怕的那个在一个昏暗的洞窟中. 墙壁上雕刻着寓言."~13|"那梦境伟大而古老. 被恐惧之约饲育着; 没人有力量拒绝它." ~14|"轮子在轮子中旋转; 一个王渴望你们的双手."~15|"有什么在下面加入了我们. 入侵者不会浮起." ~16|"一个问题不会一直得不到回答."~18|"盐墙从浪涛中升起. 他们会找到自己的墓地."~19|"当入侵者的光照亮深渊. 巨兽会醒来. 入侵者永远找不到和平; 只能找到恐惧." ~20|"会有一道新的地平线. 所有人都会知道. 但是王的城市将会第一个见证." ~12|"战士逃跑了, 在自由中让自己窒息而死."~17|"自由易碎. 巨兽会醒."
Texts.Eng: 1|"There is a question waiting. It travelled in a ship long wreck’d. Find it."~2|"The beast is tethered - but not forever. Refuge comes to London." ~3|"They were seven and they shall be seven again. Their names may change but the number remains." ~4|"The names of the heirs to Nidah will begin with M, A, R, I - which is rebellion." ~5|"Beneath the waves, two cities live. They grow. They hunger."~6|"Beware Anthe. It will change you. You will be sharp, keen as a knife’s edge."~7|"The wound reopens; the flesh will not heal. Bring them your remorse." ~8|"They yearn for it: Liberty, Equality, Eternity."~9|"They are only mortal. They suffer too: Vitality, Infirmity, Fatality."~10|"The preacher travels to the bell tower. The bell, it- Oh god. That's horrid." ~11|"The one they fear waits in a pale cavern. The walls are carved with prophecies."~13|"The dream is great and ancient. It is fuelled by deeds of horror; none will have strength to deny it." ~14|"Wheels turn within wheels; a king yearns for your hand."~15|"One joins us below. The trespasser does not surface." ~16|"A question will not go unanswered indefinitely."~18|"The Salted will rise above the waves. They will find only their graves."~19|"An ancient beast wakes when the trespasser’s light pierces the abyss. The trespasser shall never know peace; only terror." ~20|"There shall be a new horizon. All shall know it - but the king’s city will witness it first." ~12|"The Soldier fled, and smothered himself in freedom."~17|"Freedom is fragile. The beast will wake."

Texts.Chs: 1|计时树还是一棵充满希望的树苗, 刚刚长出许多嫩绿的枝芽.~2|计时树又高又壮.它的枝干伸到了屋顶上.~3|计时树开花了.白色的花瓣撒满了广场.~4|计时树开始枯萎. 它粗糙的枝干开始发出呻吟.~5|计时树断裂并倒下了.是时候回到船上了.
Texts.Eng: 1|The Tree of a Single Day is a hopeful sapling, green and budding.~2|The Tree of a Single Day is tall and strong. Its branches stretch over the rooftops.~3|The Tree of a Single Day is flowering. White petals drift across the square.~5|The Tree of a Single Day cracks and leans. It is time to return to your ship.~4|The Tree of a Single Day is withered. Its gnarled trunk groans.

Texts.Chs: 1|狩猎真理的切洛内特人上了你的船, 她急切地想查看骨雕馆的波浪
Texts.Eng: 1|The Truth-Hunting Chelonate boards your ship, where she eagerly scans the waves for Scrimshander

Texts.Chs: 1|冒险家有个请求... 和他进行进一步谈话或者查看自己的日志
Texts.Eng: 1|The Venturer has a request... speak to him further, or check your Journal

Texts.Chs: 1|巨兽在你入侵时厌恶的颤动着.
Texts.Eng: 1|The beast quivers with distaste at your trespass.

Texts.Chs: 1|巨兽蛰伏中~2|血液在水中弥漫, 渐渐散去.~3|旮旯的水中有些特别的胆汁味~4|装着恶臭气体的气泡从巨兽的胃中涌出~5|大嘴大张着, 等待猎物
Texts.Eng: 1|The beast slumbers~2|Blood hangs in the water, slowly dissipating.~3|The waters of Nook taste especially bilious~4|Foul gas bubbles up from the beast's stomach~5|The maw opens wide, awaiting prey

Texts.Chs: 1|你在赛西尔港见到的孩子想去旮旯.~2|旮旯的孩子被带回了家.~3|肺草交易商把旮旯的孩子带走了. ~4|一群旮旯人组成的暴徒袭击了你, 要求旮旯的孩子回来.~5|风流倜傥的女士让你卷入了旮旯孤儿失踪事件中.~6|风流倜傥的女士确定失踪的孩子和祭司和大嘴的震动有关.~7|麻衣人利用大嘴的震动逃到了洞窟中. ~8|除了孤儿院和矿井之外洞窟里什么都没有. 但是这两个地方都值得调查.~9|在继续探索旮旯之前你必须直面暴徒.~10|暴徒用尽了力气. 你可以继续调查旮旯.~11|是时候进入食道面对麻衣人了. ~19|麻衣人和女士都进入了食道切口.~20|麻衣人和女士在进行英雄和恶棍的角色扮演. 这个游戏带他们深入大嘴伤痕.~21|你把女士从大嘴伤痕中救了出来.~22|你把麻衣人从大嘴伤痕中救了出来.~23|你将麻衣人和风流倜傥的女士交给命运发落. 他们被吸进了大嘴的伤痕中.
Texts.Eng: 1|The child you found at Port Cecil wants to be taken to Nook.~2|The Nook child has been brought home.~3|The lungweed trader has taken the Nook child off your hands. ~4|A mob of Nookers attacked you, demanding the return of missing Nook children.~5|The Debonair Deductress has involved you in the mystery of the missing Nook orphans.~6|The Debonair Deductress is convinced there is a connection between the Maw quakes, the missing children and the masked priest.~7|The Hempen Man took advantage of the Maw quake to flee to the Cavities. ~8|There is little in the Cavities apart from an orphanage and a mine. But both might be worth investigating.~9|You'll need to face the mob before you can continue to explore Nook.~10|The mob's energy is spent. You can continue investigating Nook.~11|It is time to enter the Gullet, to confront the Hempen Man.~19|The Hempen Man and the Deductress entered the cut in the Maw.~20|The Hempen Man and the Deductress role-play hero and villain. This game has led them deep into the wound in the Maw.~21|You saved the Deductress from the Maw wound.~22|You saved the Hempen Man from the Maw wound.~23|You left the Deductress and the Hempen Man to their fates. They were sucked into the Maw wound.

Texts.Chs: 1|贫困的城市.~17|繁荣的城市!
Texts.Eng: 1|The city is in want.~17|The city is thriving!

Texts.Chs: 1|银色字迹的微光在黑暗中闪烁着. "它撕裂了心. 耻辱依旧在."~2|一个皱眉的海盗用匕首清洁他的牙齿. 刚特极点的深处对于那些能找到它的人而言是一个隐藏的好地方.~3|隧道向三个方向旋转着, 你舔舔手指, 微风在你脚边吹拂.~4|一阵清新空气冲过隧道 心脏颤抖了一会儿..~6|钙化的心脏碎片从顶部如雨般坠落.~7|心室变窄了. 石化的脂肪堆积在你的脚边~8|烛光颤抖着.在你身后的黑暗中, 有些脚步声.~9|一群老水手围坐一团, 用腐烂的牙齿撕咬着一只刚来的鲸鱼.~10|一名肠卜者的学徒快步通过 手中提着来自刚特极点深处的补给品.~11|一阵温和的低哼引导你向前，但是你的眼皮变得沉重。 附近有个可以睡觉的地方, 你可以休息, 没必要醒来.~12|你用手拂过隧道的锯齿状边缘, 另一个心室, 那些石头曾经全是血肉吗?~13|你经过了一个水手的营地. 他们看着你, 拒绝说话. 你继续向心脏深处前进.~14|水滴从顶部裂缝处滴落, 你尝了尝, 很污秽, 很咸, 就连回味也充满了卤水味. 不过还是比口渴的感觉好.~15|远处有些人吹着口哨, 旋律是水手们的船歌. 它可能是你.~16|银色字迹的微光在黑暗中闪烁着. "為終將到來的結局, 舉杯慶祝吧."~17|你经过了一面有着白垩记号的墙壁. 无论那记号记录的是日, 月, 年, 还是什么其他的东西, 记录的东西一定在这里呆了很长很长时间.~18|某一瞬间, 你看到了一丝来自远方的微光. 但当你细看, 它又消失了. ~20|每条隧道都扭曲旋转着. 在这样黑暗的地方要求一点点财宝真的很过分吗?~5|沿隧道向下走, 你经过了一名正在墙上写着什么的老水手. 在光照下, 它消失了, 只剩下黑暗, 只剩下不可辨认的黑暗.~19|你经过了一座毛皮搭的小屋, 主人在里睡觉, 轻轻呼吸着.尽管你透过大块血肉都能看到他被抛光的颅骨. 他在梦中咯咯说着什么, 然后翻了个身,开始打呼噜.
Texts.Eng: 1|The echo of silver writing glimmers in the darkness. "IT TORE OUT THE HEART. THE SHAME REMAINED."~2|A scowling pirate cleans his teeth with a dagger. The Gant Pole's depths are a fine place to hide, for those who can find it.~3|The tunnel twists into three directions. You lick your finger. The slight breeze guides your feet.~4|A gust of fetid air rushes through the tunnel. The heart shudders for a moment.~6|Slivers of calcified heart rain down from the cracked ventricle roof.~7|This ventricle narrows to a tight gap. Fossilised fat deposits crack under your feet.~8|The light of your candle flickers. In the darkness behind you, footsteps.~9|A group of Old Zailors sits in a circle, tearing strips off a recently arrived whale with their rotten teeth.~10|One of the Fading Haruspex's disciples scurries past, arms weighed down with supplies from deeper in the Gant Pole.~11|A gentle hum guides your feet forwards. Your eyes feel heavy. Somewhere here is a place you can sleep. You have earned your rest. There is no need to awaken.~12|You brush your hand against the rippled edges of the tunnel. Another ventricle. Was it flesh before it was stone?~13|You pass an encampment of zailors. They stare at you, refusing to talk. You move onwards and deeper into the Heart.~14|Water drips from a crack in the roof. You taste it. Stale and stagnant. Brine aftertaste. Still better than thirst.~15|In the distance, someone whistles a zee-shanty. It might be you.~16|The echo of silver writing glimmers in the darkness. "REJOICE, FOR THE END ALWAYS COMES."~17|You pass a wall covered in chalk-malks. Whether they mark days, years, or something else, whoever made them has been here for a very long time.~18|For a moment, you see a glow in the distance. It fades as soon as you look up.~20|Every tunnel twists and turns. Is a little treasure really so much to ask for in such a grim place?~5|Down this tunnel, you pass one of the Old Zailors writing something on the wall. In the light, it is invisible. In the darkness, illegible.~19|You pass a shack made of hide. The owner sleeps inside, gently breathing despite the polished bone of his skeleton visible through the decay and great chunks of devoured flesh. He cackles to himself about something in his dream, rolls over, and begins to snore.

Texts.Chs: 1|海浪泛着光.~50|海蝙蝠鸣叫着,它们可一点都不像鸟.~39|有什么漂浮着,面朝下.~47|一颗伪星在你的头顶正上方,闪烁了一下,然后消失了.~78|一缕微风吹过了你的发丝,然后消逝了.~81|海浪拍打着船的侧面,在深海中,有什么东西动了一下.~40|某种甲虫跑到了你的饼干上. 十分不礼貌地晃动着触角.~20|绿玻璃和玄武岩.盐和寂静.~37|灯晶灯在船首闪耀着,发出一道弧光.~30|在地平线上,一道病态的黄光亮起了一小会,然后消失了.~49|大家都在哪里? 他们去哪里了? ...他们就在这里.他们就在这里.你并不孤单.~60|远方的钟声.~100|一道蓝色的电光悠闲地爬上了烟斗. "圣伊拉斯谟的死亡之舞!" 喊声响起.~82|家. 温暖的明亮窗户, 同伴, 平静. 在最奇怪的时刻,你想家了.~90|空气在颤抖.你听到了背后的喘息声...~25|如镜面一般的黑水.从舷窗里传来踩在金属上的脚步声.~10|空气带来了阴影和盐的气味.~43|一名水手抬起了她的头, 仔细闻了闻. 空气中有血的气味. ~19|海泽的气味! 是盐,是冰霜,是地窖里的腐朽气味.这些都是黑暗的香料.~70|好像是无眼海豚一样的发光海兽在你的船四周游动着.~68|一名水手正在祈祷.~74|一道无力的海浪卷过.船摇晃了一下.~84|远方,非常非常远的地方,有人在惨叫...~86|前甲板上传来笑声.~88|烟囱中喷出了一团奇怪的浓烟.~11|空气颤抖着. 气氛有点不太对...~12|烟囱中喷出了一团浓烟.~13|前甲板上传来笑声.~14|远方,非常非常远的地方,有人在惨叫...~85|海蝙蝠鸣叫着,它们可一点都不像鸟.~16|一名水手正在祈祷.~17|像无眼海豚一样的发光海兽在你的船前游荡着~18|一排警惕的海蝙蝠倒挂在栏杆上.它们在你穿过甲板的时候一致转头看向了你.~0|到此为止,没什么特别的了.~72|一排警惕的海蝙蝠倒挂在电缆上. 它们在你穿过甲板的时候一致转头看向了你.~9|一块落石击碎了海面,就像是海怪冲出水面.不,那就是个海怪!不,那确实只是落石.~3|在地表上,阳光如以前一样普照大地,或者是谁假设如此.~5|水花飞溅.在地下海,没有安宁可言.~7|一道闪电劈过.水手们会说,风暴神正在看着你.~22|海浪里飘着许多破碎的木板和零件,就像是淹死的人的头发.~51|有什么东西在看着你~52|东方吹来的柔风. 里面混杂着松木的气味.不,这不可能.~53|海浪拍打着船的侧面.深海中,有什么东西动了一下.~54|远方,汽笛鸣响.~55|蓝色的电光慢悠悠地爬上了烟囱. "圣伊拉斯谟的死亡之舞!" 水手喊道.~150|你在这里不受欢迎. ~101|有些什么东西拂过了船体的外壳. 潜艇颤动了一下.~110|即便最亮的光也无法穿透海水来到这么深的地方. 那道光是某种荧光. ~120|空气很浑浊. 一名休班的船员正在轻声哭泣. ~130|一道光从窗口划过. 是另一艘潜艇吗?  ~140|观察穹顶下一片寂静. 领航员的呼吸声在这寂静中显得格外突兀. ~160|一声沉闷的钟声回响在船桥. 那是悲痛之钟, 现在消失了.  ~170|一群鱼从舷窗边经过. 前灯刺破黑暗, 照在鱼群身上, 它们的鳞片反射出彩虹般的光. ~200|罗盘晃动着. 你短暂偏离了航向. 那些珊瑚可不是什么可靠的路标.~190| 一副潜水服从窗边飘过.~180|周围突然变冷了. 你的舵手抱怨说身上起了鸡皮疙瘩.
Texts.Eng: 1|The waves are flecked with light.~50|Zee-bats cry out. They are nothing like birds.~39|Something drifts, face-down.~47|A false-star flares in the cavern roof directly above you; flares, and fades.~78|A tiny breeze stirs your hair, and dies.~81|Waves slap the side of the ship. Far below, something moves.~40|Some sort of beetle has invaded your morsel of ship's biscuit. It waggles its antennae impertinently.~20|Green glass and basalt. Salt and silence.~37|The glim-lamp at the prow fizzes, arcs.~30|On the horizon, a sickly yellow light glimmers for a moment, then fades.~49|Where is everyone? Where did they go? ...they're here. They're here. You're not alone.~60|Distant bells.~100|Blue lightnings crawl leisurely up the funnel. "St Erasmus dancing!" the cry goes up.~82|Home. Warmly lit windows, company, peace. Thoughts of home come at the strangest times.~90|The air trembles. A breath of change passes...~25|The glassy chop of dark water. The iron clatter of feet at the hatchway.~10|The air carries the scent of salt and shadows.~43|A zailor raises her head, sniffs sharply. Blood on the wind. ~19|The scent of the zee! Salt and frost and cellars. Black spices.~70|Luminescent beasts like eyeless dolphins play in your wake.~68|A zailor is praying.~74|A sluggish wave. The ship pitches.~84|Far off, very far off, someone screams...~86|Laughter from the fore-deck.~88|A belch of smoke goes up from the funnel.~11|The air trembles. A breath of change passes...~12|A belch of smoke goes up from the funnel.~13|Laughter from the fore-deck.~14|Far off, very far off, someone screams...~85|Zee-bats cry out. They are nothing like birds.~16|A zailor is praying.~17|Luminescent beasts like eyeless dolphins play in your wake.~18|A row of watchful zee-bats perch on the ship's railing. Their heads swivel in unison as you cross the deck.~0|That's all for now.~72|A row of watchful zee-bats hang from a cable. Their heads swivel in unison as you cross the deck.~9|A rock breaks the water like a surfacing zee-beast. No, it's a  zee-beast! No, it's a rock.~3|On the Surface, the sun still warms the Earth. Or so one assumes.~5|A brisk spatter of spray. The Unterzee is restless.~7|An electric shiver to the air. Storm is watching, the zailors would say.~22|The waves are cluttered with zee-wrack, like drowned hair drifting.~51|You are being watched.~52|A soft wind from the East. The impossible scent of pine.~53|Waves slap the side of the ship. Far below, something moves.~54|A ship's horn, far away.~55|Blue lightnings crawl leisurely up the funnel. "St Erasmus dancing!" the cry goes up.~150|You are not welcome here. ~101|Something brushes briefly against the shell. The zub shakes.~110|The brightest light cannot reach this depth. That glow is an illusion. ~120|The air is stale. An off-duty crewman keens softly. ~130|Lights glance past the windows. Another zubmarine?  ~140|The Observation Dome is silent. Your navigator's breath is loud in the stillness.~160|A dull tolling echoes around the bridge. A distress bell, now fading.  ~170|A shoal of fish pass by a porthole. The prow-lamp reveals the midnight iridescence of their scales. ~200|The compass shifts in the binnacle. Briefly, you are off-course. The coral is a useless signpost.~190| A diving-suit floats past the glass.~180|The temperature changes abruptly. Your helmsman complains about goosebumps.

Texts.Chs: 2|第二名船长已经在地下海失踪.~3|地下海从不宽恕,当然也不会宽恕你的第三名船长.~4|第四名船长, 现在,将再也无法回到伦敦.~77|失去一名船长可能是因为运气不好,但是失去七十七名船长意味着你真是太粗心了.~100|这是真的?~5|第五名船长把自己的生命献给了探索事业.~7|第七名.~8|第八名船长和其他的船长一样最终消失在了大海中.~9|第九名船长死了.让我们低头默哀,一小会就好.~10|你失去了第十名船长,但是海泽依旧很饿.~50|你经历了太多的船长.别介意:总会有更多的船长的.~51|船长太多,时间太少.~52|深海中躺满了你的先行者.~42|又失去了一名船长! 不要恐慌Don't panic.~43|你还要喂海泽多少船长?~44|海泽又带走了一名船长.没准这是他们应得的.~12|已经有一打船长被光明,时间和希望抛弃了.~13|不幸的十三.这不意味着前十二名是幸运的.~15|已经死了十五名船长了.~16|第十六.~17|第十七名船长沉入了深渊; 没错,深渊.~14|又一名船长沉默了.~25|难道阁下试着用鱼钩去钓利维坦? 用第二十五名船长? 显然失败了.~69|有些人想歪了.~53|又一名船长.~18|第十八个, 海泽还在等着你的礼物.~19|第十九名船长;黑暗中的三十八只眼睛.~20|二十名船长, 目前为止.也许他们的正在深寻王的城堡中享受着盛宴,喝着酒,说着笑话.也有可能他们的骨头正在海底沉默着.~21|二十一名船长.我们都会这样子的.~22|二十二名船长.死亡正在困扰着我.没准你也一样.~23|圣诗23 : 我虽然行过死荫的幽谷，也不怕遭害. 但是你的船长没那么幸运.~24|两打了! 我们建议你进行祭祀.~26|又失去了一名船长.~70|_另一名_ 船长沉没了.~78|他们还是会来.~11|是一名船长.要不要凑够一打?~6|已经有六名船长完成了最终的牺牲.~1|你的第一名船长死了.别担心.这种事情很正常. 用你的下一名船长继续勇敢探索吧.
Texts.Eng: 2|A second captain has been lost to the Unterzee.~3|The Unterzee does not forgive, and it has not forgiven your third captain.~4|Four captains, now, will never return to London.~77|To lose one captain may be regarded as a misfortune. To lose seventy-seven looks like carelessness.~100|Seriously?~5|A fifth captain has given their life to the cause of exploration.~7|Seven is the number.~8|An eighth captain has gone where all captains go in the end.~9|A ninth captain gone. Let us bow our heads, but only for a moment.~10|Ten captains lost, and still the zee is hungry.~50|You are getting through a lot of captains. Never mind: there are always more.~51|So many captains, so little time.~52|The deep places teem with your forebears.~42|Another captain lost! Don't panic.~43|How many more captains will you feed to the zee?~44|The zee has taken another captain. They probably deserved it.~12|A round dozen of your captains have been abandoned to light, time and hope.~13|Unlucky thirteen. Not that the previous twelve were especially lucky.~15|Fifteen captains gone.~16|Sixteen captains gone.~17|A seventeenth captain has gone down into the abyss; yea, into the abyss.~14|A zailor's dozen of captains have been lost at zee.~25|Canst thou draw out Leviathan with a hook? Perhaps with a twenty-fifth captain? Apparently not.~69|Someone has a dirty mind.~53|Another captain down.~18|An eighteenth captain, and still the zee waits for the gifts you will bring it.~19|Nineteen captains; thirty-eight eye-sockets there in the dark.~20|Twenty captains, now. Perhaps they feast around a table in the Fathomking's castle, exchanging toasts and jokes. Perhaps their bones blacken below.~21|Twenty-one captains. We will all come to this.~22|Twenty-two captains. Timor mortis conturbat me. You too, probably.~23|Psalm 23: though you walk through the valley of the shadow of death, yet shall you fear no evil. Your captain isn't so lucky, though.~24|Two dozen captains gone! We commend your dedication.~26|Another captain lost.~70|_Another_ captain down.~78|And still they come.~11|Eleven captains. Shall we make it a dozen?~6|Six captains have made their final sacrifice.~1|Your first captain has died. DON'T WORRY. These things happen. Explore boldly with your next captain.

Texts.Chs: 30|那光很明亮.~20|那光很灿烂.~40|那光令人着迷.~50|那光压迫着你.~60|那光吸引着你,无论你在哪里.~70|那光是你血液中的神秘动力.~1|那光: 太美了.~10|那光: 不像地下其他任何东西一样.~80|对于那光的回忆一直伴随着你.~90|T对于那光的回忆一直伴随着你. 继续.打开那盒子.~100|当你闭上眼睛,你看到了那光.~110|当你闭上眼睛, 你看到了那光中的影子. 是一座塔吗?~130|那塔上升,那名字开始燃烧.太阳在呼唤着你的名字.~160|那塔上升,那名字开始燃烧.忘了它.奔向太阳.~120|无论什么时候,只要你闭上眼睛,你就能看到那闪亮的高塔.名字在其中燃烧着.~200|受够了这黑暗.去向太阳那边.把你自己变成一道火光.~170|太阳像奔腾的大河一样在你的梦境中咆哮着.太美了.~180|你会升到太阳上.迷失在那里.~190|你会升到太阳上.迷失在那里. 快了,神啊,快了.~140|巨塔升起,名字开始燃烧.太阳在天顶呼唤着你的名字.但是东方究竟有什么?~150|东方吸引着你,但是天上的太阳也吸引着你.做个选择: 分解掉这个还是分解掉另一个.
Texts.Eng: 30|The light is a glory.~20|The light is a wonder.~40|The light fascinates.~50|The light compels.~60|The light draws you, constantly.~70|The light is a secret electricity in your blood.~1|The light: it's pretty.~10|The light: it's like nothing else in the Neath.~80|The memory of the light is always with you.~90|The memory of the light is always with you. Go on. Open a box.~100|When you close your eyes, you see the light.~110|When you close your eyes, you see shapes in the light. Towers?~130|The towers rise, the name burns. The Sun speaks your name.~160|The towers rise, the name burns. Forget it. Rise to the Sun.~120|Whenever you close your eyes, you see the shining towers rise. The Name burns within.~200|Enough of this darkness. Go to the sun. Give yourself like a spark to smoke.~170|The Sun growls in your dreams like a pent river. Be glad.~180|You will rise to the Sun and be lost.~190|You will rise to the Sun and be lost. Soon, O God, soon.~140|The towers rise, the name burns. The Sun speaks your name above. But what lies in the East?~150|The East draws you, but so does the Sun, high above. A choice: one dissolution or another.

Texts.Eng: 5|The Seven have found their commander.~1|The Seven need a commander.~3|Perhaps you can convince Batuk to rejoin the Seven.

Texts.Chs: 5|会有美丽出现.
Texts.Eng: 5|There will be something beautiful.

Texts.Chs: 5|欢迎!~1|有人在找船.
Texts.Eng: 5|Welcome!~1|Someone is looking for passage.

Texts.Chs: 5|这些尸体要去谁那里?~1|前往猎户塔楼.~10|前往三号要塞.~30|前往三号要塞.~15|你见证了历史.~35|按期交货.
Texts.Eng: 5|Who will the corpse go to?~1|Bound for Hunter's Keep.~10|Bound for Station III.~30|Bound for Nuncio with the Drownie Postman.~15|You witnessed history.~35|Scheduled for redelivery.

Texts.Chs: 5|你和女士已经面对面.~4|她就在这里.~10|黑女士会记住你.~1|你让你自己被记住.~2|你净化了自己.~3|你已经满足了自己.
Texts.Eng: 5|You are face to face with Her Ladyship.~4|She is here.~10|Lady Black will remember you.~1|You have made yourself known.~2|You have purified yourself.~3|You have satisfied yourself.

Texts.Chs: 5|你和流放者共进了晚餐.~10|你做了抉择.~11|你和流放者在她的房间里见了面.~20|你回答了流放者的问题.
Texts.Eng: 5|You dined with the Exile.~10|You made a choice.~11|You've visited the Exile in her cabin.~20|You answered the Exile's question.

Texts.Chs: 5|你为雪孩子起了名字~2|你和雪孩子说了话~20|雪孩子将会从伊瑞暮向东去~1|你帮助创造了雪孩子~7|雪孩子想去东方 - 如果你能防止他融化~10|你了解到雪孩子需要心金属~80|雪孩子开始了旅程~88|雪孩子回家了~99|雪孩子化了
Texts.Eng: 5|You have named the Snow Child~2|You have spoken to the Snow Child~20|The Snow Child will head East from Irem~1|You have helped create a snow child~7|The Snow Child wants to go East - if you can stop it melting~10|You have learned that the Snow Child requires Heartmetal~80|The Snow Child has begun its journey~88|The Snow Child returned home~99|The Snow Child melted

Texts.Chs: 7|七人团已经重组.~1|你已经招募了七人团中的一人.
Texts.Eng: 7|The Seven Against Nidah are reformed.~1|You have recruited someone to the Seven.

Texts.Chs: 7|这个怪兽很强壮. 它的血还在不断剧烈泵出.~6|怪兽的身体剧烈挣扎着.~5|怪兽的血变黑了, 显得油腻腻, 黏糊糊.~4|海兽的挣扎变弱了. 它不剩多少时间了.~3|海兽呻吟着. 它已经几乎没什么力气颤抖.~0|怪兽静了下来, 它的痛苦结束了.~2|海兽摇晃着, 临近结局.~1|怪兽的心最后跳动了一下.
Texts.Eng: 7|The beast is strong. Its blood pumps thick and hard.~6|The beast's body thrashes in agony.~5|The beast's blood blackens. Viscous. Oily.~4|The beast's pulse weakens. It has little time left.~3|The beast moans. It barely has the energy to quiver.~0|The beast is silent. Its pain is over.~2|The beast shakes, mewling for the end.~1|The beast's final heartbeats pound their last.

Texts.Chs: 一个海兽去了刚特极点.
Texts.Eng: A beast of the zee has gone to the Gant Pole.

Texts.Chs:
一本为孩子写的书. 每一页上都是一种地表无法找到但是却存在于地下的颜色.

[你每找到一种不可能的颜色都可以返回到监护官这里. 书页给了你一些线索, 但是你需要在远方的港口找到它们.]
Texts.Eng:
A book for children. One page is devoted to each of the colours of the Neath, which are not found on the Surface.

[Return to the Curator with each of the seven impossible colours in hand. The book's pages give you clues, but you'll need to seek far ports.]

Texts.Chs: 一箱煽动性的文件.仅仅是揭示出他们中有的人正在秘密对抗法律 .
Texts.Eng: A box of incendiary documents. Simply being aware of some of them is against laws too secret to have been written.

Texts.Chs: 满满一箱神秘的物品. 打开它!
Texts.Eng: A boxful of mystery. Open it!

Texts.Chs: 一枚猫眼琥珀的胸针,还有一个警告.
Texts.Eng: A brooch of amber cat's eyes, and a warning.

Texts.Chs: 一桶非常小,但是有着剃刀般牙齿的蛇状鱼.
Texts.Eng: A bucket of tiny but razor-toothed serpentlings.

Texts.Chs: 双木匠, 纺织工, 工程师的手,还有老鼠的所有技能.
Texts.Eng: A carpenter, weaver, engineer's hand and rat of all work.

Texts.Chs: 山洞里住满了流亡者.
Texts.Eng: A caveful of exiles.

Texts.Chs: 内置了镜子矩阵的匣子: 一个不可思议的设备,它被用来捕获阳光.
Texts.Eng: A chest with an embedded matrix of mirrors: an unlikely device for capturing sunlight.

Texts.Chs: 最终一个孩子会解出它...
Texts.Eng: A child could solve this. Eventually...

Texts.Chs: 雪孩子生于渴求之地平线.
Texts.Eng: A child of snow was born at the Avid Horizon.

Texts.Chs: 如果不包装怎么能叫雪茄.
Texts.Eng: A cigar is nothing without its wrapper.

Texts.Chs: 建立在巨兽背上一座一直在进行修补的城市. 和平的代价如此之深.
Texts.Eng: A city in constant repair, set upon the back of a great beast. The price of peace is profound.

Texts.Chs: 一箱特别的人类灵魂. 它永远也不会知道皇家海关的印章长什么样子. 因此, 它不能在市场中出售,你最好别在带着这些的时候被人抓到.
Texts.Eng: A crate of exceptional human souls. It has never known the tender touch of the Imperial Customs stamp. Consequently, it cannot be sold on the open market, and you'd better not be caught with it.

Texts.Chs: 一箱正在哀求的灵魂. 它上面没有盖海关的印章 - 这是走私货!
Texts.Eng: A crate of pleading souls. This one does not bear a customs stamp - it is contraband!

Texts.Chs: 诅咒降临到你身上: 无名的告别之神的诅咒.
Texts.Eng: A curse lies on you: the curse of the nameless god of farewells.

Texts.Chs: 诅咒降临到你身上: 高处与愤怒的无名神的诅咒.
Texts.Eng: A curse lies on you: the curse of the nameless god of high places and anger.

Texts.Chs: 一份关于达哈城中实际情况的报告.
Texts.Eng: A description of how things stand at Dahut.

Texts.Chs: 一份关于名胜古迹的详细报告.海军部会很重视的.
Texts.Eng: A detailed report on a place of interest. The Admiralty would value it.

Texts.Chs: 一只威严的琥珀色大猫, 因为其对马鲛鱼的爱好而闻名. 但是水手对待她总是带有一种夸张的尊敬. 他们见过她在镜子中的样子...
Texts.Eng: A dignified tortoiseshell-tabby, notable mainly for her fondness for mackerel. But the zailors treat her with exaggerated respect. They've seen what she looks like in a mirror...

Texts.Chs: 一个建有酒馆和蜜馆的放荡走私者巢穴.
Texts.Eng: A dissolute smugglers' haven of alehouses and honey-dens.

Texts.Chs: 一块坠落的钟乳石: 一个塞满了战利品的僧院.
Texts.Eng: A fallen stalactite: a monastery filled with plunder.

Texts.Chs: 无政府主义者最可怕的对手.
Texts.Eng: A fierce old enemy of anarchists.

Texts.Chs: 一个果实,一个珠宝,还是一滴眼泪? 让植物学家来鉴定它吧.它尝起来有点像松果.
Texts.Eng: A fruit, a jewel, a tear? Leave that distinction to the botanists. It tastes a little like pine-nuts.

Texts.Chs: 一个雕刻着南方的印记的神龛,闪闪发光.
Texts.Eng: A glittering altar carved with the Signs of the South.

Texts.Chs: 海底的一张巨口, 不法之徒与水中生物的巢穴.
Texts.Eng: A great mouth in the zee-floor, home to a lawless, aquatic culture.

Texts.Chs: 每一桶里都有一百个梦.
Texts.Eng: A hundred dreams in every barrel.

Texts.Chs: 某种荣誉.
Texts.Eng: A kind of glory.

Texts.Chs: 一些关于如何扮演这些角色的知识. [有时候, 无知即是自由. 学到更多会造成更复杂的效应.]
Texts.Eng: A knowledge of roles and how they are to be played. [Sometimes, ignorance is freedom. Learning more will have complex effects.]

Texts.Chs: 来自一位几乎已死的人的信, 给旮旯的同志的道歉.
Texts.Eng: A letter from the Almost Dead Man, apologizing to a comrade in Nook.

Texts.Chs: 来自一位几乎已死的人的信, 向隐逸之地的一位爱人告别.
Texts.Eng: A letter from the Almost Dead Man, bidding farewell to a lover in Hideaway.

Texts.Chs: 来自一位几乎已死的人的信, 向安忒的某人宣读其永恒的爱.
Texts.Eng: A letter from the Almost Dead Man, professing his undying love to one in Anthe.

Texts.Chs: 一个有着宏伟顶冠的鹦鹉,只会说那些它认为足够优秀的挽诗. 它的内心一定十分悲伤.
Texts.Eng: A majestically crested bird which speaks only in competent elegiac poetry. It is of a melancholy disposition.

Texts.Chs: 一个问题很多的人正在你的船上.
Texts.Eng: A man with many questions is on your vessel.

Texts.Chs: 一个坐落在种玫人码头的人头攒动的市场, 专门面向收集者和古怪的人营业.
Texts.Eng: A market for collectors and eccentrics throngs on Roser's Wharf.

Texts.Chs: 背了一身债的忧郁老流浪汉. 带他回家. [当你带他回伦敦时,请确认你身上有6000回声的现金.]
Texts.Eng: A melancholy old rogue with a difficult debt. Take him home. [Be sure you have at least six thousand Echoes in cash when you do.]

Texts.Chs: 来自船墟的旋律
Texts.Eng: A melody from Wrack

Texts.Chs: 一件通过死亡传递的信件. [这会安全的放在你的住所里.]
Texts.Eng: A message transmitted through the medium of death. [This is stored safely in your Lodgings.]

Texts.Chs: 上百万支点燃的蜡烛. 圣会的聚集地.
Texts.Eng: A million candles glow. A congregation gathers.

Texts.Chs: 一件古怪的心金属武器.
Texts.Eng: A monstrous weapon of monstrous heartmetal.

Texts.Chs: 共鸣与力量的名字,被抛弃在高塔之中.现在它是你的了.
Texts.Eng: A name of force and resonance, abandoned in a high tower by the one who bore it. Now it's yours.

Texts.Chs: 国家一定要强大. 如果这达到0, 皮格莫特岛上会发生不好的事情.
Texts.Eng: A nation must be strong. If this reaches 0, bad things will happen on Pigmote Isle.

Texts.Chs: 一定要建立一个国家. 如果这达到0, 皮格莫特岛上会发生不好的事情.
Texts.Eng: A nation must build. If this reaches 0, bad things will happen on Pigmote Isle.

Texts.Chs: 国家需要希望. 如果这达到0, 皮格莫特岛上会发生不好的事情.
Texts.Eng: A nation needs hope. If this reaches 0, bad things will happen on Pigmote Isle.

Texts.Chs: 一份经过公正的拷贝静静地躺在 贝斯波恩 & 福林皮尔斯法律咨询中心的保险库里.另外一份,则由大巴扎保管. [这将会确认你的下一名船长能接管你的住所,还有你存在那里的所有遗产.]
Texts.Eng: A notarised copy rests securely in the vaults of Baseborn & Fowlingpiece. Another, in the vaults of the Bazaar itself. [This will ensure your next character inherits your Lodgings, along with any Heirlooms you have stored there.]

Texts.Chs: 你的书房里挂着一幅画, 是一个熟铁打造的浮标, 永无尽头地漂浮着, 光线刺穿了海泽的黑暗.你几乎能听到那钟声. [你之前的船长越过了世界的最东方.]
Texts.Eng: A painting hangs in your study, of a wrought-iron buoy, endlessly afloat, light piercing in the Neath's dark. You can almost hear the bell. [A captain of your lineage sailed east out of the world.]

Texts.Chs: 你的书房里挂着一幅画, 看起来像是一座不可能存在的山上缠绕着的迷雾. [你之前的船长越过了世界的最东方.]
Texts.Eng: A painting hangs in your study, of mist on the face of impossible mountains. [A captain of your lineage sailed east out of the world.]

Texts.Chs: 你的书房里挂着一幅画. 两名旅者在眺望着, 永远保持着这个姿势,就像他们目的地的光已经很近了. [你之前的船长越过了世界的最东方.]
Texts.Eng: A painting hangs in your study. Two travellers watch, forever, as the lights of their destination come closer. [A captain of your lineage sailed east out of the world.]

Texts.Chs: 未透露的过往
Texts.Eng: A past yet to be revealed

Texts.Chs: 浮现出的画.
Texts.Eng: A picture emerges.

Texts.Chs: 从巴扎上切下的一小块东西, 从合法的角度看, 这是属于你的.
Texts.Eng: A piece cut from the Bazaar, legally yours.

Texts.Chs: 手工制作愉悦的地方, 所有的东西都有价可循.
Texts.Eng: A place of handmade delights, all available for a price.

Texts.Chs: 一种笨重但是货仓很大的船.
Texts.Eng: A ponderous, capacious vessel.

Texts.Chs: 一座监狱岛. 或者瘤节先知的食品柜.
Texts.Eng: A prison island. Or the knot-oracles' larder.

Texts.Chs: 为骨雕馆而生的沉默溺亡者, 要将生命献给研究.
Texts.Eng: A quiet drownie borne for Scrimshander, to dedicate his life to research.

Texts.Chs: 一个变节的粘土女在海泽上游荡，掠夺弱小船长的船只。
Texts.Eng: A renegade Clay Woman roams the zee, pillaging the ships of weaker captains.

Texts.Chs: 为可汗的荣耀准备的报告
Texts.Eng: A report for Khan's Glory

Texts.Chs: 一份关于爱古处Fortas Kettle中正在进行的事情的报告.
Texts.Eng: A report of doings in the Fortas Kettle at Aigul.

Texts.Chs: 一份关于那盛开的港口中诸多事务的报告.
Texts.Eng: A report of the doings in the flourishing port.

Texts.Chs: 引擎困住了一头怒吼的巨兽.
Texts.Eng: A roaring beast of an engine.

Texts.Chs: 一个从好战的豚鼠维亚家来的很有学者风度的生物,那里的贵族先知先觉地偷到了一艘蒸汽船,逃出了伦敦评论家即将锁上的笼子.  这很显然.
Texts.Eng: A scholarly creature from a warlike nation of aristocratic guinea-pigs whose progenitors stole a steamer to escape the locked hutches of a London essayist.  Apparently.

Texts.Chs: 知识的一个碎片. [发现怪物和地点来获得碎片.足够数量的碎片可以合成秘密.]
Texts.Eng: A scrap of lore. [Discover monsters and locations to gain Fragments. Gain enough Fragments, and they'll combine into a Secret.]

Texts.Chs: 对那些跟屁虫很有用.
Texts.Eng: A severe disincentive to pursuit.

Texts.Chs: 一个阴影中的人给了你一个提议.
Texts.Eng: A shadowy figure has made you an offer.

Texts.Chs: 一个用玻璃和钢铁制造的复杂机器,闪着光. 在它的核心,一只蛇王怒吼着. 也许是魔术师在哀求着.
Texts.Eng: A shimmering complexus of steel and glass. In its heart, a serpent-king rages. Or so the Magician claims.

Texts.Chs: 猫岛海盗王对你信任的象征.
Texts.Eng: A sign of the trust of the Pirate-King of the Isle of Cats.

Texts.Chs: 一个看起来很阴险的小雕像... 但是它的眼神却带着某种恳求.
Texts.Eng: A sinister little squatting image... but its eyes are pleading.

Texts.Chs: 一块从天而降伤痕累累的陨铁, 有一辆独轮车那么大.它的两侧有发光的符文.
Texts.Eng: A sky-scarred hunk of meteoric iron, the size of a wheel-barrow. Burning glyphs mark its flanks.

Texts.Chs: 一大块从天而降的陨铁, 一辆手推车的大小. 在它的侧面闪着符文的火花.一个星星的种子在它里面. 它在看着你.你确定你知道你要拿这东西来做什么吗?
Texts.Eng: A sky-scarred hunk of meteoric iron, the size of a wheel-barrow. Burning glyphs mark its flanks. A star-spore lives in it. It's watching you. Are you sure you know what you're doing with this thing?

Texts.Chs: 一个微笑,一个眼神, 一个蝴蝶纹身. 对武器和引擎有着热情与专业知识.
Texts.Eng: A smile, a wink, a butterfly tattoo. An intense and detailed knowledge of weaponry and engines.

Texts.Chs: 一份对于当地事物不甚全面的描述.
Texts.Eng: A somewhat less than frank and full description of affairs.

Texts.Chs: 关于孤立和归属的歌, 同样歌唱了伟大之物和人性.
Texts.Eng: A song of isolation and belonging, of greatness and humility.

Texts.Chs: 关于暗流和泥沙的歌.
Texts.Eng: A song of undertows and silt.

Texts.Chs: 来自深处关于崇拜与爱慕的歌.
Texts.Eng: A song of worship and adoration from the depths.

Texts.Chs: 一个覆叶的继承人切下的部分.
Texts.Eng: A souvenir of one of the Cladery Heir's amputations.

Texts.Chs: 一堆笔记本, 上面是用珍贵的墨水写的密密麻麻的东西.
Texts.Eng: A stack of notebooks, closely written in treasure-ink.

Texts.Chs: 尾巴上的毒刺.
Texts.Eng: A sting in your tail.

Texts.Chs:
研究空地中间那棵不可能生长在地下的树, 关于一名船长撕毁画着大蛇的画像. 船长的船员在旁边冷静地观看着. 其中一个人口中分叉的舌头清晰可见. 绘画上被涂满了琉璃绿 - 半梦半醒的颜色, 这种颜色在地面无法看到.
你就是画中的船长; 你也是作画的那个人.
Texts.Eng:
A study of a clearing amid trees that do not grow in the Neath, of a zee-captain smashing the image of a painted serpent. The zee-captain's crew look on calmly. A forked tongue is visible in one's open mouth. The painting is tinted everywhere with viric - the greenish colour of shallow sleep, which cannot be seen on the surface of the world.
You are the zee-captain in the painting; you are also the painter.

Texts.Chs: 里面溢出了一些愤怒的光.有些时候它会发出咯咯声.最好不要打开它.
Texts.Eng: A sullen viric glow leaks from within. Sometimes it rattles. Best not open it.

Texts.Chs: 一个会思考的生物制作了它, 或者是大海冲刷出来的; 或者二者皆有.
Texts.Eng: A thinking creature made this, or the sea made this; or both.

Texts.Chs: 在汗国进行交易的许可证.
Texts.Eng: A token permitting you to trade in the Khanate.

Texts.Chs: 实用主义考古学家的工具.
Texts.Eng: A tool for pragmatic archeologists.

Texts.Chs: 胜利? 悔恨? 无论如何, 这都会留在你心中.
Texts.Eng: A triumph? A regret? Either way, it lingers in your mind.

Texts.Chs: 外交官,商人和富裕的间谍喜欢使用的型号.
Texts.Eng: A vessel for diplomats, merchants and wealthy spies.

Texts.Chs: 一团发出嘶嘶声的蒸汽困扰着你
Texts.Eng: A watchful hissing vapour haunts you

Texts.Chs: 一份爱情小说被安忒最好的意识修订.
Texts.Eng: A work of romantic literature that has been revised by the best Anthean minds.

Texts.Chs: 一个海怪镇纸, 用阴暗黑骨雕得很漂亮. [你之前的船长被证明是海怪之子]
Texts.Eng: A zee-monster paperweight, beautifully carved from Stygian ivory. [A previous captain in your lineage proved to be the child of a zee-monster]
AK to add quality reqs and other mechanics.

Texts.Eng: Acquiring a Zubmarine

Texts.Eng: Adam's Way: a Guest at a Red Table

Texts.Eng: Adam's Way: the Tree of a Single Day

Texts.Chs: 用闪闪发光的战利品装点你的大厅.  [在它到达5之前, 你一直可以用工艺品提升财富.]
Texts.Eng: Adorn your hall with glittering trophies.  [Until this reaches 5, you can keep improving your Estate with Artefacts.]

Texts.Chs: 建议在等着你. [你从Fallen London游戏中得到了这: 它对所有的新角色都有用.]
Texts.Eng: Advice awaits you. [You acquired this from Fallen London: it'll be available for all new characters.]

Texts.Eng: Aigul: Commissioned to Retrieve a Regret

Texts.Chs: 爱古: 大副的敏感
Texts.Eng: Aigul: First Mate's Sensitivity

Texts.Chs: 爱古: 关于大副问题的知识
Texts.Eng: Aigul: Knowledge of the First Mate's Question

Texts.Chs: 爱古: 棘刺要塞
Texts.Eng: Aigul: Needle of Fortas

Texts.Chs: 白色的修补匠
Texts.Eng: Albino Tinkerer

Texts.Chs: 所有的都很丰裕,所有的都很充实.
Texts.Eng: All foison, all abundance.

Texts.Chs: 所有的东西尚未真正失去.
Texts.Eng: All is not quite lost.

Texts.Chs: 我们所有人都需要吃东西.
Texts.Eng: All of us must eat.

Texts.Chs: 所有心的历险都在这里, 用散文,诗歌或者绘画. 有些也许更适合私人享用. [附注:在伦敦, 所有的爱情故事都要缴税.即使是虚构的爱情故事也一样.]
Texts.Eng: All the adventures of the heart are here, in prose, poetry or pictorial form. Some may be more suitable for private consumption. [Note: in London, customs duty is paid on love stories. Even illustrated love stories.]

Texts.Chs: 所有的地狱之火, 还有所有的天堂之馨.
Texts.Eng: All the fire of Hell, and all the aroma of Heaven.

Texts.Chs: 结局好就万事大吉，微光是从相对幸福的结局中获得的。
Texts.Eng: All's well that ends well. Gleam is gained from relatively happy endings.

Texts.Chs: 几乎安全了
Texts.Eng: Almost Safe

Texts.Chs: 含混的石器
Texts.Eng: Ambiguous Eolith

Texts.Eng: Ambition: the Seven, Anew

Texts.Eng: Ambition: the Walls of Nidah

Texts.Chs: 你身上一个不显眼的额外眼睛
Texts.Eng: An Additional Eye on an Unobtrusive Part of your Person

Texts.Chs: 有些象古物的藏宝图
Texts.Eng: An Ancient-Ish Treasure Map

Texts.Chs: 不可破坏的遗嘱
Texts.Eng: An Ironclad Will

Texts.Chs: 一个不太可能的综合治疗方法
Texts.Eng: An Unlikely Collection of Treatments

Texts.Chs: 不讨人喜欢的团块
Texts.Eng: An Unprepossessing Mass

Texts.Chs: 一名年老的猎人来到了骨雕馆, 寻找她祖先的伟大故事.
Texts.Eng: An aging hunter borne for Scrimshander, searching for the great tales of her ancestors.

Texts.Chs: 古代的愤怒现在知道了你的存在.
Texts.Eng: An ancient anger knows you.

Texts.Chs: 一团正在滴下液体的可怕有机物,从你不愿去想的那些地方拿出来的.
Texts.Eng: An appalling glob of organic matter and dripping fluids, retrieved from somewhere you'd rather not think about.

Texts.Chs: 一位切除专家.
Texts.Eng: An expert in amputations.

Texts.Chs: 一块银色金属锭, 摸起来极其寒冷.
Texts.Eng: An ingot of silvery metal, dreadfully cold to the touch.

Texts.Chs: 一份和令人愉快的女探险家会面的邀请. (这将继续手掌帝国的故事)
Texts.Eng: An invitation to meet the Delightful Adventuress at the University. (This continues the Empire of Hands story)

Texts.Chs: 一处奇怪的地方，最好留意一下。
Texts.Eng: An odd place. Best to keep an eye on it.

Texts.Chs: 一种孤游器官，曾由孤游器官驾驶。
Texts.Eng: An orphaned organ, once piloted by an organ orphan.

Texts.Chs: 一位不动感情的人, 喜欢摆弄标本针和那些玻璃罐, 他正在寻找罕见的鳞翅目昆虫.
Texts.Eng: An unsentimental man of pins and the jar, in pursuit of rare lepidopterae.

Texts.Chs: 一面从海泽远方的迷你国家来的不平凡的旗帜.
Texts.Eng: An unusual flag from a tiny nation far across the zee.

Texts.Chs: 生物学展示柜
Texts.Eng: Anatomical Cabinet

Texts.Chs: 这是一块黎明机器喷出或加工出的东西, 它的运动并未随着离开黎明机器而停止.
Texts.Eng: And yet it moves. A piece, emission or work of the Dawn Machine.

Texts.Eng: Another Day: A Free Evening

Texts.Chs: 另一天: 令人惊恐的学者的信
Texts.Eng: Another Day: A Message from the Alarming Scholar

Texts.Chs: 另一天: 新船员?
Texts.Eng: Another Day: A New Recruit?

Texts.Chs: 另一天: 盲眼壮汉来访
Texts.Eng: Another Day: A Visit from a Blind Bruiser

Texts.Chs: 另一天: 遗骨和可怕的故事
Texts.Eng: Another Day: Dead Bones and Dread Tales

Texts.Chs: 另一天: 在残骸中

Texts.Eng: Blood oozes slowly from the flesh around it, and is drawn into the scar.

Texts.Chs: 出生或者领养, 他们是你的.
Texts.Eng: Born, sired, or adopted, they're yours.

Texts.Chs: 秘密和囚犯都被囚禁在其中.
Texts.Eng: Both secrets and prisoners are locked here.

Texts.Chs: 加快呼吸并没有用. 头痛并未消退. 耳鸣不断, 再过一会就好了吗?
Texts.Eng: Breathing faster doesn't help. That stinking headache won't shift. And could the ringing in your ears stop, just for a moment?

Texts.Chs: 明亮, 黑暗, 暴躁, 温柔, 富裕, 绝望. 一个复杂的地方: 就像伦敦一样.
Texts.Eng: Bright, dark, fierce, soft, rich, desperate. A complicated place: like London.

Texts.Chs: 把一名船官带给深寻王. 选择一名完成了海上事务的船官, 而且想要留在深寻王的堡垒里的人. 也许某个喜欢海鲜的家伙会想要这么做.
Texts.Eng: Bring an Officer to the Fathomking. Choose someone who has finished their business on the zee, and might be willing to stay in the King's court. Probably someone who likes fish.

Texts.Chs: 带来一件卓越的引擎或者武器.你的船官会帮上忙的.
Texts.Eng: Bring an engine or weapon of unique brilliance. Your Officers can help.

Texts.Chs: 为深寻王带来阳光... 或者那些可以冒充阳光的东西.

Texts.Eng: Did a Judgement hatch from this grim relic? Or was it something else entirely. Don't look too closely at the eye-hurting absence of colour.

Texts.Chs: 确保没人能在没有钥匙的情况下进去...或者出来.[这能防止你的货物被贪婪的乘客偷走,或者让你安全的运输一些活东西.]
Texts.Eng: Ensure that no-one gets in without the key. In... or out.[This will help protect against acquisitive passengers and over-lively cargo.]

Texts.Chs: 确保发动机不会在开足马力时爆炸.
Texts.Eng: Ensures your ship's engine won't explode at Full Power.

Texts.Chs: 装备并在海中使用它来挑战海盗诗人.
Texts.Eng: Equip and use it at zee to challenge the Pirate-Poet.

Texts.Chs: 即使是海盗王也会很受用这些礼节
Texts.Eng: Even Pirate-Kings like their courtesies

Texts.Chs: 每天它都会融化一点.
Texts.Eng: Every day, it melts a little more.

Texts.Chs: 每分每秒, 每日每周, 每月, 每年 对他而言都是痛苦.
Texts.Eng: Every second of every minute; hour; day; week; month; year; is an agony to him.

Texts.Chs: 每艘船都有自己的秘密.
Texts.Eng: Every ship has its secrets.

Texts.Chs: 每一步都引领你通向结局.
Texts.Eng: Every step leads to your final destination.

Texts.Chs: 每人都有个梦.
Texts.Eng: Everyone has a dream.

Texts.Chs: 一切都很可能很好
Texts.Eng: Everything is Probably Perfectly All Right

Texts.Chs: 一切都很安静. 那可能意味着一切都还好.
Texts.Eng: Everything is quiet. That probably means that everything is fine.

Texts.Chs: 对死信办公室里的值班工作很有经验.
Texts.Eng: Experienced in shift work at the Dead Letter Office.

Texts.Chs: 实验与修改

Texts.Chs: 探索海洋.走私丝绸和灵魂.吞噬你的船员.
Texts.Eng: Explore an ocean. Smuggle silk and souls. Devour your crew.

Texts.Chs: 大副探索爱古苦恨时的悔恨具现.
Texts.Eng: Expressions of the First Mate's grief at exploring the bitterness of Aigul.

Texts.Eng: Get Rats Where Rats Are Required, Pneumatically. [In combat, this can deploy Rattus Faber assistants for quicker repairs.]

Texts.Chs: 快回来. 快回来! 不要直视它!
Texts.Eng: Get back. Get back! Don't look at it directly!

Texts.Chs: 像盐一样锋利,像冰一样透明的玻璃.
Texts.Eng: Glass as clear as ice and sharp as salt.

Texts.Chs: 去往港口劝说船长开往船墟上方水域.
Texts.Eng: Go to the port and convince a few captains to zail over Wrack.

Texts.Chs: 上帝保佑不朽的女王陛下.
Texts.Eng: God bless Her Enduring Majesty, the Empress.

Texts.Chs: 一群愤愤不平的年轻人加入了想要杀死大嘴的狂热者队伍
Texts.Eng: Groups of disaffected youth are joining a cult which seeks the death of the Maw

Texts.Eng: Has he warmed to you? Or is he considering the possible uses of your organs?

Texts.Eng: Has she found a hiding space amongst the spores?

Texts.Chs: 那个纹身在你上次看到他之后又变大了?
Texts.Eng: Has that tattoo grown since last you looked?

Texts.Eng: Has the Cladery Heir performed a treatment?

Texts.Eng: Has the Fierce Philanthropist's husband been in Aigul?

Texts.Eng: Has the Fierce Philanthropist's husband been in Scrimshander?

Texts.Chs: 暴躁的慈善家的丈夫去船墟了吗?
Texts.Eng: Has the Fierce Philanthropist's husband been in Wrack?

Texts.Chs: 忧心忡忡的医生
Texts.Eng: Haunted Doctor

Texts.Chs: 你和覆叶的继承人正在找什么吗?
Texts.Eng: Have you and the Cladery Heir been looking for something?

Texts.Chs: 你变成安忒的港口报告了吗?
Texts.Eng: Have you turned in a Port Report of Anthe?

Texts.Chs: 你是否使用晶化来强化特别的技能?
Texts.Eng: Have you used your sharpness to enhance a particular skill?

Texts.Chs: 他能让这些补给可以入口, 尽管不是很美味.
Texts.Eng: He can render the supplies edible, if not palatable.

Texts.Chs: 他宣称对对抗尼达的七人众没有一点兴趣. [将这个属性降低到0来改变他的态度.]
Texts.Eng: He claims he has no interest in the Seven Against Nidah. [Reduce this to 0 to change his mind.]

Texts.Chs: 他从不接受失败的傻瓜.
Texts.Eng: He does not tolerate fools or failure.

Texts.Chs: 他有着极为强烈而糟糕的希望.
Texts.Eng: He has a mighty and terrible hope.

Texts.Chs: 他有个计划.
Texts.Eng: He has a plan.

Texts.Chs: 他对海鲜烹饪很有野心. 而且是巨大的野心.
Texts.Eng: He has an ambition for fish. A great ambition.

Texts.Chs: 他要求你揭露智慧监狱的典狱长, 并要求去隐逸之地.
Texts.Eng: He has requested you unmask the Governor of Wisdom and demand he come to Hideaway.

Texts.Chs: 他有着把敌人的墓土压实后的那种满意笑容.
Texts.Eng: He has the quiet smile of a man who has tamped down the earth on his enemy's grave.

Texts.Chs: 他将他的复仇暂时搁置.
Texts.Eng: He has turned aside from his revenge.

Texts.Chs: 他有时会出现在死亡侨居地
Texts.Eng: He may sometimes be found in the Tomb-Colonies

Texts.Chs: 他可能不会锯错腿.
Texts.Eng: He probably won't saw the wrong limb off.

Texts.Chs: 他曾经相信过一些事情.
Texts.Eng: He used to believe in things.

Texts.Chs: 他想要...
Texts.Eng: He wants...

Texts.Chs: 他在被绘画时不会不戴帽子.
Texts.Eng: He wouldn't be painted without his hat.

Texts.Chs: 他一直在看着.他不会眨眼.
Texts.Eng: He's always watching. He doesn't blink.

Texts.Chs: 他非常关心精神世界.
Texts.Eng: He's deeply concerned with spiritual matters.

Texts.Chs: 他对他的同伴心存感激.
Texts.Eng: He's grateful for the company.

Texts.Chs: 他见人们战斗过, 见人们为自己的目标献身. 现在, 他正在找一名隐逸之地的幸存者.
Texts.Eng: He's seen what people have fought and died for. Now he seeks the ones who survived at Hideaway.

Texts.Chs: 红心值
Texts.Eng: Hearts

Texts.Chs: 继承物
Texts.Eng: Heirloom

Texts.Chs: 她的眼睛很快就会孵化. 但是在那之前, 她想要工作.
Texts.Eng: Her eyes will hatch soon. But until then, she wants to work.

Texts.Chs: 她的大限快到了.
Texts.Eng: Her time draws nearer.

Texts.Chs: 她的诗或许结束了.
Texts.Eng: Her verses may be complete.

Texts.Chs: 英雄来来去去, 但是他们的故事被混乱的年代淹没, 被潮水冲刷. 骨雕大厅的溺亡者会向你支付大量报酬来换取幽暗储藏库中特别的故事.
Texts.Eng: Heroes come and go, cast up by turbulent times and washed away by the next tide. The Drownie Chorus in Scrimshaw's amphitheatre will pay you handsomely to uncover these patterns from the tales in the Ivory Archives.

Texts.Chs: 赫斯珀里得斯苹果
Texts.Eng: Hesperidean Apple

Texts.Chs: 隐逸之地是个转折点. 有些东西很快会失去控制.
Texts.Eng: Hideaway is at a turning point. Something will give way soon.

Texts.Eng: Hideaway: Celebrating a Festival

Texts.Chs: 隐逸之地: 决定隐逸之地的未来
Texts.Eng: Hideaway: Deciding the Future of Hideaway

Texts.Chs: 隐逸之地: 隐逸地的难民
Texts.Eng: Hideaway: Hideaway Refugees

Texts.Chs: 隐逸之地: 不礼貌的调查员
Texts.Eng: Hideaway: The Impolite Investigator

Texts.Chs: 隐逸之地: 愉快的梦想家的野心
Texts.Eng: Hideaway: The Sprightly Visionary's Ambition

Texts.Chs: 隐逸之地: 愉快的梦想家的请求
Texts.Eng: Hideaway: The Sprightly Visionary's Request

Texts.Chs: 隐逸之地: 真相
Texts.Eng: Hideaway: The Truth

Texts.Chs: 隐逸之地: 时间流逝
Texts.Eng: Hideaway: Time Passing

Texts.Chs: 隐逸之地: 对你的堤防
Texts.Eng: Hideaway: Wary of You

Texts.Chs: 如果你是个没有原则的人,这能给你带来很多利润. [这东西就算是合法使用也太过危险. 把它带到伦敦时要格外小心.]
Texts.Eng: Highly profitable, if you have no principles. [This stuff is too dangerous even to be properly illegal. Be cautious in taking it to London.]

Texts.Chs: 他的主人远行至此寻找烟草.
Texts.Eng: His master went far in pursuit of a cigar.

Texts.Chs: 他烹饪的海鲜能让皇帝落泪.
Texts.Eng: His mastery of fish-flesh would make an emperor weep.

Texts.Chs: 举起一面镜子看着镜子中的它: 一只豹子的幼崽, 身上长着像午夜雾气一样的灰色绒毛,但是透着琥珀的光泽.
Texts.Eng: Hold up a mirror and see its other self: a panther cub, grey as night-fog but touched with amber.

Texts.Chs: 无家可归!
Texts.Eng: Homeless!

Texts.Chs: 怎么可能有这样的一件东西? 除了你还有谁能明白它的意思?
Texts.Eng: How can such a thing be? Who but you could understand what it means?

Texts.Chs: 罗西娜距离因燃魂病而死还有多远?
Texts.Eng: How close is Rosina to death by animescence?

Texts.Chs: 荣耀的结局是什么? 骨雕记录者告诉你那些故事都能在历史的海滩上找到.
Texts.Eng: How did the Glory meet its end? The Scrimshaw Chronicler told you that the tale can be found on history's beach.

Texts.Chs: 他们怎么称呼你?
Texts.Eng: How do they speak to you?

Texts.Chs: 你究竟想要什么? [这决定了你的胜利方式: 尽管你随时可以选择在伦敦退休作为一种折中的选择.]
Texts.Eng: How do you want it all to end? [This determines how you win: although you can always just retire in London, for a draw.]

Texts.Chs: 这个几乎已死的人如何面对他的死亡?
Texts.Eng: How does an Almost Dead Man face his end?

Texts.Chs: 你要走多远去寻宝?
Texts.Eng: How far down will you go in search of treasure?

Texts.Chs: 小伦敦的消费怎么样?
Texts.Eng: How fares Little London?

Texts.Chs: 你在达哈度过的时间?
Texts.Eng: How long have you spent in the fields of Dahut?

Texts.Chs: 你已经变晶化了多少部分?
Texts.Eng: How many places have you gone sharp?

Texts.Chs: 你的船上有多少水手?
Texts.Eng: How many zailors do you have aboard?

Texts.Chs: 一个生物还有多少生命与健康.
Texts.Eng: How much health a creature has.

Texts.Chs: 在没东西可供拿取之前, 你能提供多少?
Texts.Eng: How much of yourself can you give before there is nothing left to take?

Texts.Chs: 你可以忍受多少晶化?
Texts.Eng: How much sharpness can you endure?

Texts.Chs: 你有多少空间?
Texts.Eng: How much space do you have?

Texts.Chs: 你的违禁品在搜查官的搜查下有多安全?
Texts.Eng: How secure is your contraband against excisemen?

Texts.Chs: 你的货舱安全吗?
Texts.Eng: How secure is your hold?

Texts.Chs: 你对罗欣娜了解多少?
Texts.Eng: How well do you know Rosina?

Texts.Chs: 你对福塔斯.凯特的大副了解多少?
Texts.Eng: How well do you know the First Mate of the Fortas Kettle?

Texts.Chs: 你的建议是?
Texts.Eng: How will you advise?

Texts.Chs: 你如何击败长老议会无穷的军队?
Texts.Eng: How will you overcome the Presbyter's numberless legions?

Texts.Chs: 你的王国会被人怎么称呼?
Texts.Eng: How will your kingdom be known?
Hull

Texts.Chs: 饥饿
Texts.Eng: Hunger

Texts.Chs: 狩猎蓝色先知或者衣帽商蝙蝠来获取这个.
Texts.Eng: Hunt Blue Prophets or Milliner-Bats to find these.

Texts.Chs: 猎人之眼
Texts.Eng: Hunter's Eye

Texts.Chs: 狩猎战利品
Texts.Eng: Hunting-Trophy

Texts.Chs: 我閃耀 / 至墜落
Texts.Eng: I SHINE / TO DESCEND

Texts.Chs: 如果你胆敢使用这个, 那就把它带去伦敦
Texts.Eng: If you dare to use this, take it to Fallen London

Texts.Chs: 若你从来都没有过,你也不会丢失它.
Texts.Eng: If you'd never had it, you'd never miss it.

Texts.Chs: 如果你足够幸运,它只会杀了你.
Texts.Eng: If you're lucky, it will only kill you.

Texts.Chs: 不可能!
Texts.Eng: Impossible!

Texts.Chs: 我们这个时代最惊人的巧合, 鱼雷是 '鱼形'的. [鱼雷射击需要的弹药.]
Texts.Eng: In one of the most striking coincidences of our times, torpedoes are 'torpedo-shaped'. [Ammunition for Torpedo Salvoes.]

Texts.Chs: 只要一两个,就能让你开心与振奋.但是吃得太多有可能让你体验到世间最美妙的死法.
Texts.Eng: In smaller quantities, delightful and refreshing. In larger quantities, one of the very nicest ways to die.

Texts.Chs: 领先
Texts.Eng: In the Lead

Texts.Chs: 在这些石头巨兽的缝隙里, 真菌虫开始成长.
Texts.Eng: In the creases of the great stone beast, blemmigans sprout.

Texts.Chs: 在山的深处放置着一枚光滑的金色蛋. 每小时一次, 它会慢慢的毫无生机地跳动一下.
Texts.Eng: In the depths of the mountain lay a great egg of smooth gold. Once every hour, it pulses with slow and deadly life.

Texts.Chs: 在伦敦的屋顶上, 日历会谋划着终结法律的统治.
Texts.Eng: In the roof-tops of London, the Council conspires to end the rule of law.

Texts.Chs: 通过在达哈的互动提升.
Texts.Eng: Increase this at Dahut, through interaction there.

Texts.Chs: 在玛瑙港的隐蔽工房将其提升至 100 来将你的船变形为潜艇.
Texts.Eng: Increase this to 100 at the hidden workshop in Port Carnelian to convert your ship to a zubmarine.

Texts.Chs: 在老鼠值降到1之前将其提升至50...
Texts.Eng: Increase this to 50 before Mouse reaches 1...

Texts.Chs: 在老鼠值降到1之前把你的猫值提升到50...
Texts.Eng: Increase your Cat to 50 before this reaches 1...

Texts.Chs: 不屈的军医
Texts.Eng: Indomitable Campaigner

Texts.Chs: 来自卡米安运河的信息
Texts.Eng: Information from the Cumaean Canal

Texts.Chs: 来自钢铁和米斯里合作公司的情报
Texts.Eng: Information from the Iron and Misery Company

Texts.Chs: 把小伦敦消息带给伦敦.
Texts.Eng: Information on Little London for Fallen London.

Texts.Chs: 鼓舞,治疗,防御. [有时这会对恐惧相关的判定有帮助.]
Texts.Eng: Inspire, heal, defend. [Sometimes helps with tests around Terror.]

Texts.Chs: 从硫磺公约中搜集的情报,那是地狱的流亡政府.
Texts.Eng: Intelligence gleaned from the Brimstone Convention, the government-in-exile of Hell.

Texts.Chs: 在安忒和罗欣娜互动.
Texts.Eng: Interact with Rosina at Anthe.

Texts.Chs: 阴谋也许会给你在这个国家生存下去的手段. [在它到达 5之前, 你一直可以用关键情报提升你的财产.]
Texts.Eng: Intrigue might give you the leverage you need to survive as a nation. [Until this reaches 5, you can keep improving your Estate with Vital Intelligence.]

Texts.Chs: 有趣的片段
Texts.Eng: Intriguing Snippet

Texts.Chs: 很值得怀疑.这么少的人是怎么弄丢那么多的悲伤蜘蛛的?
Texts.Eng: Intriguing. How could so many people have missed so many sorrow-spiders?

Texts.Chs: 调查旮旯: 神经紧张的人
Texts.Eng: Investigating Nook: A Bundle of Nerves

Texts.Chs: 调查旮旯: 麻衣人
Texts.Eng: Investigating Nook: A Hempen Man

Texts.Chs: 调查旮旯: 糟糕的钻头
Texts.Eng: Investigating Nook: A Vile Drill

Texts.Chs: 调查旮旯: 失踪的补给
Texts.Eng: Investigating Nook: Missing Supplies

Texts.Chs: 调查旮旯: 无力者
Texts.Eng: Investigating Nook: The Nerveless

Texts.Chs: 调查旮旯: 孤儿院
Texts.Eng: Investigating Nook: The Orphanage

Texts.Chs: 和覆叶的继承人一同调查
Texts.Eng: Investigating with the Cladery Heir

Texts.Chs: 不可战胜之印章
Texts.Eng: Invictus Token

Texts.Chs: 参与到特定的交易中.
Texts.Eng: Involvement in a certain trade.

Texts.Chs: 钢铁值
Texts.Eng: Iron

Texts.Chs: 桀骜不驯的炮手
Texts.Eng: Irrepressible Cannoneer

Texts.Chs: 她的丈夫在回忆之城吗?
Texts.Eng: Is her husband at the City of Remembrance?

Texts.Chs: 她将正义带给了海盗之林的海盗们吗?
Texts.Eng: Is she bringing justice to the pirates of Corsair's Forest?

Texts.Chs: 她在这些半死不活的人之中工作吗?
Texts.Eng: Is she working amongst the nearly-dead?

Texts.Chs: 有什么对你造成的恐惧更甚于死亡吗?
Texts.Eng: Is there anything you fear more than death?

Texts.Chs: 麻衣人是旮旯的居民吗? 他和震动有什么关系?
Texts.Eng: Is this Hempen Man a Nooker? What is his connection to the Maw quakes?

Texts.Chs: 这是...一个灵魂? 它十分苍白而明亮. 他们说,像这样的灵魂是一个奇怪神明的孢子.
Texts.Eng: Is this... a soul? It's pale and bright. Souls like this, they say, are the spores of strange gods.

Texts.Chs: 你的颅骨足够锐利吗?
Texts.Eng: Is your skeleton as keen as it could be?

Texts.Chs: 你的舌头是一块软钻石吗? 你的言语闪光吗? 你的言语锐利吗?
Texts.Eng: Is your tongue a supple diamond? Does your speech glitter and stab?

Texts.Chs: 猫岛: 伊瑟琳的赞助
Texts.Eng: Isle of Cats: Isery's Patronage

Texts.Chs: 猫岛: 铁笼女士的赞助
Texts.Eng: Isle of Cats: Lady of the Cages' Patronage

Texts.Chs: 猫岛: 走私红蜂蜜
Texts.Eng: Isle of Cats: Smuggling Red Honey

Texts.Chs: 猫岛: 海盗王的通知
Texts.Eng: Isle of Cats: The Pirate-King's Notice

Texts.Chs: 它在等待一个短语来打开它。
Texts.Eng: It awaits the phrase that will open it.

Texts.Chs: 它闪着月蓝色的光. 为了争夺这样一块蓝色闪晶,人们不惜发动战争. [你能找到这东西的用处: 也许令人惊恐的学者会购买这东西.]
Texts.Eng: It blazes with apocyanic radiance. Wars have been fought for less. [You may find a use for this: or the Alarming Scholar will certainly purchase it.]

Texts.Chs: 回味起来有点苦.
Texts.Eng: It can leave a bitter aftertaste.

Texts.Chs: 它发着柔光. 足够照亮你进入旮旯的路程.
Texts.Eng: It glows softly. Enough to light your way in Nook.

Texts.Chs: 它确实有锋利的爪子; 上面有吓人的钩状物; 但是现在它看起来并不想用它的爪子.
Texts.Eng: It has claws; it has a fierce double beak; but just now it seems disinclined to use them.

Texts.Chs: 它被精心地上了一遍漆, 它的眼睛闪着光, 看起来让人很有食欲.
Texts.Eng: It is beautifully enamelled. Its eyes glisten like digestive fluid.

Texts.Chs: 这很难得.
Texts.Eng: It is hard-earned.

Texts.Chs: 融化是它的本质.
Texts.Eng: It is in its nature to melt.

Texts.Chs: 它不会轻易表现出来的.
Texts.Eng: It is not given lightly.

Texts.Chs: 它在早晨被种下, 中午就长得很高了,下午出现花蕾,在晚间枯萎. 外国人必须在它倒下之前回到船上.
Texts.Eng: It is planted in the morning, grows tall by lunch, buds in the afternoon, and withers in the evening. Foreigners must return to their ships before it falls.

Texts.Chs: 这是能冲上岸的最可怕也最罕见的东西.
Texts.Eng: It is rare something so awful washes up on shore.

Texts.Chs: 据说有七个人试图将不朽普及.
Texts.Eng: It is said that seven once tried to democratise death.

Texts.Chs: 据说如果你需要打破达哈的幻境, 那么你需要吃掉它. 但是请小心.
Texts.Eng: It is said you may eat it if you ever need to break an illusion at Dahut. But be cautious.

Texts.Chs: 很幸运, 它正在睡.
Texts.Eng: It is, fortunately, sleeping.

Texts.Chs: 这能制造最大规模的爆炸. 不是你所想要的优雅兵器, 但是它能制造最强烈的爆炸. [威严型是只能向前射击的火炮: 其他的是鱼雷和鱼叉类武器.]
Texts.Eng: It makes the most tremendous bang. Not what you'd call an elegant weapon, but it does make the most tremendous bang. [The Majesty is the only front-mounted pure cannon: others are torpedoes or flensing weapons.]

Texts.Chs: 它有可能是某种鱼,但是最好不要离太近看.
Texts.Eng: It might be some sort of fish, but best not to look too closely.

Texts.Chs: 它只能持续这么长时间...
Texts.Eng: It only lasts so long...

Texts.Chs: 这看起来并没有坏处; 最坏会发生什么?
Texts.Eng: It seems innocuous enough; what's the worst that could happen?

Texts.Chs: 更疼了. [一旦你的伤势达到3, 你就会死. 在住处休息会治愈你, 有时海中的事件也会治愈.]
Texts.Eng: It stings rather. [If you ever have three Wounds, you're dead. They will heal when you rest in your Lodgings, and from time to time at zee.]

Texts.Chs: 它扑通扑通，飘来飘去，散发着令人愉悦的气味. [这艘船玩家将在日后以更高的领航等级返回无光之海时可用. 它将在日后DLC中开放.]
Texts.Eng: It thrums. It wanders. It has a delightful stink. [This ship is available players who backed Sunless Sea at the Navigator Tier or higher. It will become available as DLC at a later date.]

Texts.Chs: 这曾经是个好地方. 好吧,并没有那么好.
Texts.Eng: It was a nice place once. Well, no it wasn't.

Texts.Chs: 一名不善言辞的将军把那里命名为玛瑙港. 之后她发现那里到处都是蓝宝石. 想想她对此有多尴尬.
Texts.Eng: It was the Laconic General who named the Carnelian Coast. Then she discovered it was full of sapphires. Imagine her embarrassment.

Texts.Chs: 这也是第一版. [你之前的船长完成了一部关于海泽的史诗.]
Texts.Eng: It's a first edition, too. [A captain of your lineage wrote the definitive work of maritime literature.]

Texts.Chs: 这可能是件好事?
Texts.Eng: It's a good thing. Probably?

Texts.Chs: 它不是个有吸引力的东西. 也许你不会把它留在壁炉架上.
Texts.Eng: It's not an attractive object. Perhaps you won't keep it on your mantelpiece.

Texts.Chs: 它非常危险, 但是既然它如此美丽,又有谁在乎呢?
Texts.Eng: It's very dangerous, but who cares when it's so pretty?

Texts.Chs: 它在很远的地方;但是也许它在注意着你.
Texts.Eng: It's very far away; but perhaps it's watching you.

Texts.Chs: 它在看着你; 如果它真的存在.
Texts.Eng: It's watching you; if it even exists.

Texts.Chs: 它的兄弟姐妹抛弃了它. 珍珠色的光从它的头冠上发出. 珊瑚之源曾经碰过它, 而且是用不那么温柔的方法. 但是它烹饪鱼肉和盐的手法简直就是个奇迹...
Texts.Eng: Its brothers and sisters have abandoned it. Pearly light drips from its mantle-crest. The Principles have touched it, and not gently. But it can work miracles with salt and fish-flesh...

Texts.Chs: 它的眼中闪着警惕的光. 它的忧郁已经消散: 现在你似乎有了某种预感.
Texts.Eng: Its eyes glitter with awareness. Its melancholy has dissipated: now you sense anticipation.

Texts.Chs: 它的坏脾气让它失去了船员的宠幸,但是这也让它成为了一只很有效率的捕鼠者 .
Texts.Eng: Its perpetual ill temper does not endear it to the crew, but it does make it an effective ratter.

Texts.Chs: 它的双翅承载了几千年的记忆.其中只有一小部分是美好的记忆.
Texts.Eng: Its wings carry a thousand years of memories. Few of those memories are good.

Texts.Chs: 司命共鸣管
Texts.Eng: Judgement Resonator

Texts.Chs: 你能多相信她?
Texts.Eng: Just how far can you trust her?

Texts.Chs: 囚徒之蜜会打开多少扇门? 这会为你开启Zero Summer (查看上方提示条)的一个额外初始选项 以及其他StoryNexus 的游戏世界...
Texts.Eng: Just how many doors does Prisoner's Honey open? This may unlock additional starting options in Zero Summer (see the bar above) and other StoryNexus worlds...

Texts.Chs: 他们的问题具体是什么?
Texts.Eng: Just what precisely is their problem?

Texts.Chs: 当然是雅各书. 其中一段被红墨水圈了起来, 墨迹已经很久了 - 罗马书 6:9. [你的前任船长之一实现了不朽, 或者推翻了不朽.]
Texts.Eng: King James' edition, of course. One passage is circled in old red ink - Romans 6:9. [A previous captain in your lineage once achieved immortality, or turned it down.]

Texts.Eng: Legend. Enigma. She has an appointment in Polythreme.

Texts.Chs: 透镜, 药酒, 蜡烛, 火油.偶尔, 需要骨头.
Texts.Eng: Lenses, tinctures, candles, flammable oils. Now and then, bones.

Texts.Eng: Light as a thought, and jewel-bright

Texts.Chs: 像人类的心, 但不是很像.毕竟,最后,她只是粘土.
Texts.Eng: Like a human heart, but not very. After all, in the end, she was only clay.

Texts.Chs: 长长的绑在一起的船只为流亡者提供了避难所.
Texts.Eng: Long-moored ships provide shelter for exiles.

Texts.Eng: Longshanks Gunner

Texts.Chs: 看着它如何在水中滑行. 就像月光一样.

Texts.Chs: 事实上,不是奇迹. 但是他们永远不能接近到能看出其中的差别的距离.
Texts.Eng: Not miracles, really. But they'll never get close enough to see the difference.

Texts.Chs: 与其说是尸体, 不如说是一件刚脱下的西装. 尽管如此, 他在德莫港的兄弟也许想知道.
Texts.Eng: Not so much a corpse as a discarded morning-suit. Nonetheless, his brother at Port Demeaux will want to know.

Texts.Chs: 看起来威严的旅行作家去到哪里, 哪里就会发生非常引人注意的事情.
Texts.Eng: Notable stories seem to turn up where the August Travel-Writer goes.

Texts.Chs: 深海学院题头的信纸. 他想和你谈谈.
Texts.Eng: Notepaper from Benthic College. He'd like to speak to you.

Texts.Chs: 没什么能在这里扎根.
Texts.Eng: Nothing will take root here.

Texts.Chs: 现在他有了目标.
Texts.Eng: Now he has a cause.

Texts.Chs: 你们究竟是在哪里遇到的, 又一次?是纹身师克拉瑟莫特介绍你们认识的吗?
Texts.Eng: Now where exactly did you meet, again? Did Clathermont the tattooist introduce you?

Texts.Chs: 现在你能离近看, 他看起来像是一张新纸上沾了一些... 咖啡味道的东西?
Texts.Eng: Now you look more closely, it appears to be new parchment stained with what smells like... coffee?

Texts.Chs: 喔, 你这恶棍. [这会在你进行犯罪活动或者解除犯罪分子时增加.你的怀疑值越高, 税务官就会越频繁并且越仔细地搜查你的船.]
Texts.Eng: Oh, you rapscallion. [This will increase as you conduct criminal activities or have contact with rough sorts. The higher your suspicion, the more fiercely the Excise will search your ship.]

Texts.Chs: 啊呀! [黑墨镜将军会想要看到这个, 如果海军对你的好感足够高.]
Texts.Eng: Oho! [The Dark-Spectacled Admiral will want to see this, if your Admiralty's Favour is high enough.]

Texts.Chs: 苍老的灵魂啊. 你要去哪里, 苍老的灵魂?
Texts.Eng: Old soul. Where are you going, old soul?

Texts.Chs: 老皮格莫特
Texts.Eng: OldPigmote

Texts.Chs: 第一眼看上去,它就像是死亡侨民的棺材. 经过仔细检查, 它上面的铭牌上写着苏瑟 & 库珀 还有如下的标签: '遞送到 倉庫 (A), 3号要塞'.
Texts.Eng: On first sight, it looks like a tomb-colonist coffin. On closer examination, it carries stencilling reading SOOTHE & COOPER and a handwritten tag: 'DELIVERY TO DEPOT (A), STATION III'.

Texts.Chs: 在伦敦影响力的边缘,一些奇怪的事情发生了.
Texts.Eng: On the very edge of London's influence, curious matters are conducted.

Texts.Chs: 曾经明亮过,但是瓦尔查斯现在沉默在黑暗中.这种寂静显然带有恶意.
Texts.Eng: Once bright, Varchas is now dark. The silence is malevolent.

Texts.Chs: 未来的某一天,这将会是你的国家的旗帜. [装配到附属物槽位.]
Texts.Eng: One day, this will be your nation's flag. [Equip to an Auxiliary slot.]

Texts.Chs: 有人会记下船墟的歌.
Texts.Eng: One may record the song in Wrack.

Texts.Chs: 一根或多根你的指骨都能从骨雕馆白骨墙上换取故事. 至于你的手...没什么是一双填了料的手套掩饰不了的.
Texts.Eng: One or more of your finger-bones tells your tale in the ivory walls of Scrimshander. Nothing a stuffed glove can't conceal.

Texts.Chs: 你不在的时候,你需要一名管理者.
Texts.Eng: One rules in your absence.

Texts.Chs: 这些遗骨看起来和普通的骷髅没什么两样,但是你知道这些骨头究竟是谁的.
Texts.Eng: One set of bones looks much like another, but you know whose these really are.

Texts.Chs: 一个水手的宝藏对另一个水手来说就是垃圾.但是这看起来很有意思...
Texts.Eng: One zailor's treasure is another zailor's junk. But this looks interesting...

Texts.Chs: 城堡只有一小部分可以看见. 但是你能从来来往往的人那里了解到许多关于谁来过这里的信息.
Texts.Eng: Only a tiny portion of the Hold is visible. But you can learn much from the comings and goings of those who visit.

Texts.Chs: 只有长时间在安忒活动才会让你得到安忒人的能力.
Texts.Eng: Only long work at Anthe will gain you an Anthean advantage.

Texts.Chs: 只有切洛内特人对这个有食欲.
Texts.Eng: Only the Chelonate could find this appetising.

Texts.Chs: 赶走旧法则, 迎进新法则.
Texts.Eng: Out with the old laws, in with the new.

Texts.Eng: Outlying colonies are often eager for this. [You can't collect more than one Recent News at a time.]

Texts.Eng: Pearly light still drips from its mantle-crest. But it has survived the Principles... and won something in the process.

Texts.Chs: 也许她害怕被忘记. 但是除此之外她无所畏惧.

Texts.Chs: 也许你的真菌虫会在米希尔的光照下行走.

Texts.Eng: Seal of the Red Science

Texts.Chs: 用蜡层层密封.
Texts.Eng: Sealed and triple-sealed with wax.

Texts.Chs: 用一根丝带封起. 总之那看起来像是一根丝带.
Texts.Eng: Sealed with a ribbon. It looks like a ribbon, anyway.

Texts.Chs: 搜寻水下城市来寻找暴躁的慈善家失踪的丈夫.
Texts.Eng: Search the cities of the deep for the Fierce Philanthropist's missing husband.

Texts.Eng: Searing Enigma

Texts.Chs: 秘密
Texts.Eng: Secret

Texts.Chs: 秘密被埋进了血与骨中.
Texts.Eng: Secrets are buried in flesh and bone.

Texts.Chs: 安全货柜
Texts.Eng: Secure Compartment

Texts.Chs: 多愁善感而且沉溺于过去, 就像靛紫被琥珀囚禁一样,它被靛紫束缚着.哀悼着那些逝去的心灵.
Texts.Eng: Sentiments and histories coil, prisoned by irrigo as the irrigo is prisoned by amber. Mourn the mind that has passed.

Texts.Chs: 平静的水族箱
Texts.Eng: Serene Aquarium

Texts.Chs: 把它放到你的罗盘上,  用海蝙蝠的血喂它. 它会指引你的.
Texts.Eng: Set it on your binnacle,  feed it the blood of zee-bats. It will guide you.

Texts.Chs: 阴暗的厨师
Texts.Eng: Shady Cook

Texts.Chs: 她有要去骨雕馆的理由. 她也有个理由要去刚特极点. 她几乎已经下定了决心.
Texts.Eng: She had a reason for coming to Scrimshander. And she has a reason for travelling to the Gant Pole. She's almost sure of it.

Texts.Chs: 她有她的答案. 该回到何方了.
Texts.Eng: She has her answer. It is time to return to Whither.

Texts.Chs: 她对见血表示无所谓. 但是她非常不喜欢衣服上的血污.
Texts.Eng: She has no difficulties with blood. But she very much dislikes bloodstains.

Texts.Chs: 她在伦敦外的远方狩猎, 既针对其他的海盗, 也针对那些旅行太远的旅者.
Texts.Eng: She hunts far from London, picking off both other pirates and travellers who zailed too far.

Texts.Chs: 她知道火焰的用法. 但是她并不适应海泽. 把她带到伦敦, 去黄铜大使馆.
Texts.Eng: She knows the uses of fire. But she's not cut out for the zee. Take her to London, and the Brass Embassy.

Texts.Chs: 她从没真正笑过.
Texts.Eng: She never quite smiles.

Texts.Chs: 她更喜欢人们称她为花园女士. 或者蔷薇就好.
Texts.Eng: She prefers Lady of the Gardens. Or just Zaira.

Texts.Chs: 她在玛瑙港等你.
Texts.Eng: She waits in Port Carnelian.

Texts.Chs: 她在黑暗中等待着.
Texts.Eng: She waits in the dark.

Texts.Chs: 她是猎户塔楼的三姐妹中最年轻的. 现在她已无家可归. 她不会向你展示她的脸, 更不会说发生了什么,但是她已经准备好用她的知识治愈你的船员...
Texts.Eng: She was the youngest sister of the Hunter's Keep three. Now her home is gone. She will not show her face, nor speak of what occurred, but she is prepared to use her education to help heal your crew...

Texts.Chs: 她看起来比以前阴郁了一些.
Texts.Eng: She's a little more sombre than she used to be.

Texts.Chs: 她正在瓦解, 但是至少她离终点不远了.
Texts.Eng: She's falling apart, but at least she doesn't have far too go.

Texts.Chs: 她曾给将军们看病,也曾和军队一起行军. 千万别惹她.
Texts.Eng: She's marched with armies and cured generals. Don't annoy her.

Texts.Chs: 她还没为这样的一场战斗做好准备!
Texts.Eng: She's not ready for a fight like this!

Texts.Chs: 很显然,她是硫磺公约的一名守卫.
Texts.Eng: She's the guardian of the Brimstone Convention. Apparently.

Texts.Chs: 发出炽热的星海黄色光. 它吸收着不属于这个世界的辐射. 它的一些颜色只能在梦中看到.
Texts.Eng: Sizzling with cosmogone light. It has absorbed radiations not of this earth. Some of its colours can only be seen in sleep.

Texts.Chs: 狡猾的领航员
Texts.Eng: Sly Navigator

Texts.Chs: 小而敏捷,令人畏惧,就像一只发怒的野鼠.
Texts.Eng: Small, swift and formidable, like a very angry vole.

Texts.Chs: 铁匠的苦恼
Texts.Eng: Smith's Anguish

Texts.Chs: 柔和的灯晶灯
Texts.Eng: Soft Glim-Lamp

Texts.Chs: 如静谧本身一般柔软.
Texts.Eng: Soft as silence.

Texts.Chs: 柔和的嗓音和一点点神秘. 她能看见多少?
Texts.Eng: Soft-spoken and a little mystical. How much does she see?

Texts.Chs: 在谎言与夸大之词中一定隐藏着些许真相.
Texts.Eng: Some truth may be gleaned amidst exaggeration and falsehood.

Texts.Chs: 伦敦的某人需要你的帮忙.
Texts.Eng: Someone in London requires your services.

Texts.Chs: 有人想上船!
Texts.Eng: Someone wants to sign on!

Texts.Chs: 有人会拜访你的住所.
Texts.Eng: Someone would like to call on you at your Lodgings.

Texts.Chs: 有些东西发生了严重的错误.
Texts.Eng: Something has gone TERRIBLY WRONG.

Texts.Chs: 有些事情发生了,或者只是有些人宣称发生了.
Texts.Eng: Something has happened, or so somebody claimed.

Texts.Chs: 发生了一些事情.
Texts.Eng: Something has occurred.

Texts.Chs: 伊瑞暮的有些东西令人难以理解. 它真的能保护你免受太阳光的伤害吗?
Texts.Eng: Something inexplicable from Irem. Will it really protect against sunlight?

Texts.Chs: 有些东西会在达哈生长.
Texts.Eng: Something might grow in Dahut.

Texts.Chs: 有些银色的东西在他的眼中闪烁着.
Texts.Eng: Something silver looks out through his eyes.

Texts.Chs: 来自红衣主教的非常特别之物
Texts.Eng: Something very special from the Red Eminence

Texts.Chs: 一些活蹦乱跳的奇怪生物. 它被安全的囚禁着,只是可能.
Texts.Eng: Something wriggling and peculiar. It's safely confined, probably.

Texts.Chs: 有时候可以在伦敦雇用他, 但他更经常出现在遥远北方的某个港口.
Texts.Eng: Sometimes available for hire in London, or in a distant port of the North.

Texts.Chs: 有时候可以在伦敦雇用, 或者去羊岛找他.
Texts.Eng: Sometimes available for hire in London, or more reliably at the Shepherd Isles.

Texts.Chs: 有时可在伦敦雇佣.
Texts.Eng: Sometimes available for hire in London.

Texts.Chs: 有时候它也会潜伏在伦敦的港口里.
Texts.Eng: Sometimes lurking on the docks of London.

Texts.Chs: 不要提起它.
Texts.Eng: Speak not of it.

Texts.Chs: 说出正确的密语, 齿轮就会排成一列为盒子解锁. 但是正确的密语是什么? [令人惊恐的学者也许会知道些什么.]
Texts.Eng: Speak the right phrase, and the tumblers will align and unlock it. But what is the right phrase? [The Alarming Scholar may have some ideas.]

Texts.Chs: 不确定性调谐: 相比于技术,更多的只是理论. [调谐器不影响你隐匿的能力.]
Texts.Eng: Speculative Consonance: less than a technique, more than just a theory. [The Consonator does not limit your ability to hide.]

Texts.Chs: 不确定性调谐器
Texts.Eng: Speculative Consonator

Texts.Chs: 速度,隐藏,欺诈. 降低敌人能够发现你的距离.
Texts.Eng: Speed, stealth, deception. Decreases the range at which enemies will spot you.

Texts.Chs: 关于海浪和海浪下面的奇怪故事.那些海浪之下的要更奇怪些.
Texts.Eng: Strange truths are told of the waves and what lies beneath. The lies are even stranger.

Texts.Eng: Strategic Information

Texts.Chs: 严格上来讲, 这根本不应该卖给平民的船只, 但是海军的纪律最近越来越松散了.
Texts.Eng: Strictly speaking, this shouldn't be sold to civilian vessels at all, but the Admiralty has grown more casual of late.
